{"id": "3679", "revid": "26489601", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3679", "title": "P-4 Senator", "text": "The P-4 Senator is a double-action revolver in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" It features a six-round cylinder, firing from the bottom chamber, as well as a low-profile red dot sight and a rail-mounted flashlight beneath the barrel.\nIt can be unlocked on the first page of &lt;a href=\"Steeled%20Veterans\"&gt;Warbond: Steeled Veterans&lt;/a&gt; for 15 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;Medals&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nAs of the recent patch, the Senator had several buffs, the most notable of which, is making it penetrate heavy armor, the only sidearm so far capable of doing so. This puts the Senator in a unique position, as it can now harm the likes of Hulks and Bile Titans, and being powerful enough to quickly put down fodder enemies with a few well-placed shots.\nThis makes the Senator a true marksman's sidearm, as it's slow reload speed and small magazine size makes it very punishing with missed shots, it's power and precision will not disappoint to those who can quickly and rapidly find their marks.\nUnique to itself, the Senator is reloaded one round at a time if there are rounds still in the cylinder. However, if reloading from a fully emptied cylinder, a 6-shot speedloader is used, which instantly replenishes all 6-rounds in one go. Making it more advantageous to reload the Senator on empty, during combat."}
