{"id": "6034", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6034", "title": "Peacock", "text": "Peacock is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Sten%20Sector\"&gt;Sten Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Veld\"&gt;Veld&lt;/a&gt;.\nNamed for the male &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peafowl\"&gt;peafowl&lt;/a&gt; bird due to it's vibrant blue and green coloring seen by ships in high orbit, planet Peacock is a &lt;a href=\"Biomes%23Shadowed%20Jungle\"&gt;Shadowed Jungle&lt;/a&gt; class world found on the far edge of the eastern galactic rim. Covered in dense flora obscured by a perpetual twilight, the strange subversion of photosynthesis that sustains the oddly-hued flora that flourishes on this planet remains an intriguing mystery to the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth's&lt;/a&gt; greatest exo-biologists.\nIn any case, the nocturnal conditions have done little to slow the local &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; outbreak, meanwhile localized geomagnetic storms has caused a series of ion storms in the planet's upper atmosphere, which have damaged and disabled local communications and electronics utilized by &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;S.E.A.F.&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver&lt;/a&gt; forces stationed on the planet.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Liberty Tide.\nLocated in the Sten sector of the eastern part of the known galaxy, Peacock was overrun by the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; during the initial Terminid Outbreak on February of 2184. The entire sector was quarantined by &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;Super Earth High Command&lt;/a&gt;, and any attempts to retake them were put on hold near indefinitely, until the main outbreak could be contained.\nHowever following the re-opening of FTL lanes between the &lt;a href=\"Sten%20Sector\"&gt;Sten&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi&lt;/a&gt; Sectors on September 2nd 2184, as well as the final liberation of &lt;a href=\"Trandor\"&gt;Trandor&lt;/a&gt; on September 21st, the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;S.E.A.F.&lt;/a&gt; would set foot on Peacock for the first time in over seven months. However progress towards clearing the planet over the following days was negligible, with the Helldiver and army forces present barely even making a dent in the Terminid numbers. Even so, High Command is hopefully for a breakthrough as it would open up FTL lanes deeper into terminid controlled space."}
{"id": "3765", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3765", "title": "Pelican-1", "text": "Pelican-1 is the call sign used by a space shuttle from and &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It arrives at the end of every mission to extract the players back to the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;.\nLore.\nThe Pelican shuttles are tiltwing single-stage-to-orbit transport shuttles, with a 30mm autocannon mounted underneath the cockpit on the front of the vessel. Pelicans are restricted to vertical take off and landing due to the design of their landing gear.\nPelican shuttles have an internal crew compartment that can transport up to four Helldivers at a time, with two additional seats in the cockpit for the pilot and another crew member (occasionally heard cheering during autocannon fire).\nHeavy cargo\u2014such as the &lt;a href=\"EXO-45%20Patriot%20Exosuit\"&gt;Patriot Exosuit&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"EXO-49%20Emancipator%20Exosuit\"&gt;Emancipator Exosuit&lt;/a&gt;\u2014can be latched to the bottom of the Pelican for transport. Pelicans can also carry up to twenty civilian passengers, or a large quantity of E-710.\nAlthough the Pelican shuttles' engines seem to be just jet engines, they are apparently capable of both atmospheric and vacuum operation, suggesting they are actually some type of advanced rocket engine, combined-cycle engine (featuring both airbreathing and closed-cycle operation modes), or are nuclear thermal jets. Whatever engine type it may be, it must be incredibly efficient; the design of the shuttles suggests very little fuel volume (at least, very little fuel volume compared to what one would expect from a single-stage-to-orbit spacecraft).\nGameplay.\nThe shuttle arrives after 2-4 minutes from calling in an extraction at the end of a mission. Extraction time depends on mission difficulty and mission modifiers. At least one Helldiver must remain near the extraction beacon during the process, or Pelican-1 will call off the extraction attempt, forcing Helldivers to re-request extraction. Upon arrival, the shuttle starts firing its powerful frontal gun at nearby enemies.\nA Pelican-1 performing extraction will remain on the pad until surviving Helldivers enter the shuttle, or mission time expires. At this point, a 20-second countdown begins before Pelican-1 is forced to return to the Super Destroyer.\nThough functionally indestructible, the shuttle has a health pool and can catch on fire and become unusable after enduring a certain amount of damage, and may depart immediately. This typically happens only when traitorous Helldivers directly attack the shuttle."}
{"id": "4144", "revid": "54761251", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4144", "title": "Penta", "text": "Penta is one of the four planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Lacaille%20Sector\"&gt;Lacaille Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Penta is noted to house several caustic chemical factories, vital in the production of the &lt;a href=\"RL-77%20Airburst%20Rocket%20Launcher\"&gt;RL-77 Airburst Rocket Launcher&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nAlthough a seemingly a lifeless grey rock from orbit, the topography of Penta is actually comparable to some of the massive boreal and primeval forests of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super-Earth&lt;/a&gt; prior to the last great war, though obviously less colorful and much less dense.\nThe density of the planets foliage can range from being sparse to surprisingly dense, with rocky outcroppings, freezing rivers, drooping evergreen palms and colorless Cycad plants breaking up the banks of perpetual fog that cover the planet. The only natural color to be found comes from a verity of violet flowers that grow from strange, parasitic outcroppings.\nDespite its somewhat 'uncomfortable' temperatures, Petra is quite forgiving compared to other, more hostile planets, with it's abundant native foliage, plentiful water sources and an atmosphere that won't \"immediately\" freeze a human as soon as they step outside their habitats. Thus Penta is one of the many planets colonized by the Federation of Super Earth. \nThis planet could be compared with &lt;a href=\"Nivel%2043\"&gt;Nivel 43&lt;/a&gt;, since they have relatively similar flora and climatic conditions. \nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Invasion of &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;.\nOn April 9th 2184, an invasion fleet of Automaton warships conquered Cyberstan and the entirety of the Valdis Sector then quickly began a massive offesive against the planets of the neighboring &lt;a href=\"Lacaille%20Sector\"&gt;Lacaille Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The defenses of the Penta-&lt;a href=\"Chort%20Bay\"&gt;Chort&lt;/a&gt;-&lt;a href=\"Choohe\"&gt;Choohe&lt;/a&gt; Line quickly collapsed, which led to the defense campaign at the Menkent-Lesath line. The few remnants of the SEAF, alongside with what little Helldivers that could be deviated to it, valiantly and heroically held out against the Automaton onslaught, but were inevitably overwhelmed by the 26th of April as all supply lines to the planet fell to Automaton control.\nOperation Legitimate Undertaking.\nThe citizens of Penta; loyal and unwavering in their commitment to the cause of Super Earth, were able to produce, synthesize and store tons of caustic chemicals vital for the production of a new support weapon strategem: the &lt;a href=\"RL-77%20Airburst%20Rocket%20Launcher\"&gt;RL-77 Airburst Rocket Launcher&lt;/a&gt;. Production of these chemicals continued right up until prior to, during, and even after the planets fall.\nHowever with &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; forces closing in on the last holdouts, as well as the colonists of neighboring Choohe also calling for help, it is likely that only the citizens and weaponry of the first planet liberated would have been saved.\nThe Helldivers would reach liberate Lesath on the evening of April 26th, securing a supply line that then allowed them to reach Penta on the 27th. With 90% of the planet's chemical factories secured, fleetwide distribution of the RL-77 could now commence. Most of the chemical technicians who had been trapped on the planet were rescued. Tragically though, some had already perished by the time we reached them, having succumbed to the toxic fume poisoning. The &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; showed no hesitation in the use of chemical warfare against civilians, but the sacrifice of these heroic martyrs shall never be forgotten.\nHowever due to the weapons still being prototypes, the airburst rocket launchers had some ... notable teething problems.\nExperimental Launchers.\nThe first of these was an overly sensitive proximity fuze in the airburst warhead, which caused it to detonate much sooner than it was supposed to (sometimes as soon as it left the launcher, which isn't helped by Penta being a planet full of small rocks and trees). Secondly was the high spread and blast range of the scattering cluster munitions, which although good for destroying large groups of enemies, also had a habit of killing the weapons user, along with their team and everything else withing 30-40 meters. Finally was the mishandling of the weapon by the Helldivers themselves, who aimed it directly at a target (similar to an &lt;a href=\"EAT-17%20Expendable%20Anti-Tank\"&gt;EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"GR-8%20Recoilless%20Rifle\"&gt;GR-8 Recoilless Rifle&lt;/a&gt;) rather than ABOVE the target as intended, which when combined with the previous two bugs results in a lot of friendly fire incidents.\nNever the less, the weapon still has promise with those who used the weapon properly reporting positive feedback, with at least one Helldiver reporting to the Ministry of Defense that they destroyed a &lt;a href=\"Factory%20Strider\"&gt;factory strider&lt;/a&gt; using it (firing between the legs of the walker with the shell detonating under it's vulnerable underbelly). The Ministry of Science have taken note of feedback on the weapon and promise a fix to the proximity cluster warhead when the weapon goes into full production in a weeks time, but until then the Helldivers will have to deal with a slightly... moody weapon.\nSecond Galactic War.\nFailure of the Terminid Control System.\nDespite the success of Operation Legitimate Undertaking, Penta's liberation would be short-lived. Just as the Helldivers prepared to push towards Merak, the Terminid Control System in the Barrier planets and the fall of Meridia would be the final nail in its coffin. As the bulk of the Helldiver Corps was diverted away to contain the monstrous supercolony, the Automaton Front collapsed, and Penta would be invaded and recaptured by the robotic menace during the month of May.\nEver since, it lays in bondage with the rest of the Lacaille Sector's planets."}
{"id": "6184", "revid": "55381251", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6184", "title": "PersonalOrderData", "text": " \"Status\": \"ongoing\",\n \"Targets\": [\n \"type\": \"Unknown\",\n \"faction\": null\n ],\n \"Expiration\": \"0H 0M\",\n \"Rewards\": []"}
{"id": "4968", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4968", "title": "Phact Bay", "text": " is one of the six planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nSupercolony Spore Outbreak.\nAfter the failure of the TCS on April 30th the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; Supercolony began to output massive amounts of interstellar spores. Outbreaks began across the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Eastern Front&lt;/a&gt;, including in the &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt; fell on the 7th of May. Following this, the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; would almost immediately afterward attack &lt;a href=\"Pandion-XXIV\"&gt;Pandion-XXIV&lt;/a&gt; which fell on the 8th of May. &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt; would come under attack on the 10th, and with most &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyers&lt;/a&gt; being distracted elsewhere, fell with little resistance. \nOperation Destiny Manifested.\nSporadic fighting would continue on Phact Bay, with little progress being made by the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;, this was until &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Operation%20Destiny%20Manifested\"&gt;Operation Destiny Manifested&lt;/a&gt; was launched on the 4th of June. &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; was liberated, followed by &lt;a href=\"Erata%20Prime\"&gt;Erata Prime&lt;/a&gt; then &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;. This left just &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt;, which was liberated on June 7th, completing Operation Destiny Manifested. With this, the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; foothold in &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt; would be eliminated. Bringing managed democracy and freedom once more to all planets in &lt;a href=\"Jin%20Xi%20Sector\"&gt;Jin Xi Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nOperation Jin Xi - Falstaff Lockdown.\nThe liberty obtained for Phact Bay would not last for long. Due to the massive loss of lives during Operation Enduring Peace, the Helldivers had to constantly shift back and forth between fronts, often losing progress in one front to regain it in another. While the Helldivers were occupied in the Automaton Front amidst its expansion into the Trigon and Xzar Sectors, the Terminids would launch a craven assault in the evening of June 23rd, overwhelming its defenses and occupying it for 5 days.\nOnce the Helldivers managed to repel the robotic menace, they would return en masse to the rescue of the Jin Xi and Falstaff sectors, with Phact Bay's liberation now being part of the objectives of the major order issued by the Super Earth High Command. As such, Phact Bay would be liberated by June 28th, with the Helldivers managing to liberate the planet and successfully repel a surprise attack coming in from nearby Gatria, which had fallen to a spontaneous Terminid outbreak.\nOperation Overrun.\nPhact Bay would remain thriving in freedom ever since, its colonist beginning to undertake repairs and resettlement of the desert planet once more, while the war continued on in the neighboring sectors. However, this peace would not last for very long. From June to August, partly thanks to Pandion-XXIV also remaining free, Phact Bay would remain untouched by the war until, on September 1st, 2184, it would be assaulted by Terminids coming from the recently lost Pandion XXIV, almost right after the colonial overseer had restored its FTL supply lines with Gar Haren and Partion, a planet in the Sten Sector that had been lost during the initial Terminid outbreak in February 2184.\nWith the Gloom being found to be sending an augmented Terminid outbreak onto the Jin Xi Sector, Super Earth High Command would issue a major order calling for the Helldivers to retain control of Phact Bay, Gatria and Gar Haren while preventing any further spread of Terminid infestation.\nPhact Bay's defense would manage to repel the incoming Terminid forces by September 3rd, shortly after Gatria's defense concluded. However, their newly opened front with the Sten Sector, through neighboring Partion, would show it an ugly surprise.\nPartion, alongside all the other planets in the Sten Sector, had been lost during the initial Terminid outbreak of February 2184, which left whatever Terminid activities ocurred inside unable to be monitored by SEAF Reconnaissance Satellites. Even then, nothing could prepare Phact Bay for what would occur next. In the morning of September 4th, with Gatria already defending against the second biggest Terminid superonslaught ever, Phact Bay would be attacked by a massive Terminid force, only smaller than Gatria's assaulting brood by mere quirk of the numbers but still being the third biggest Terminid force ever faced by Super Earth, behind the ones encountered at Gatria and &lt;a href=\"Socorro%20III\"&gt;Socorro III&lt;/a&gt; earlier in August.\nPhact Bay would manage to successfully repel the Terminid Superonslaught. However, the Terminids at Partion then sent a second assault towards Phact Bay shortly after. This second assault would not be very notable but was still pretty intense, as Phact Bay had to be left slightly less guarded in order to help Gatria repel a second consecutive Terminid Superonslaught. Nevertheless, the defenses at Phact Bay held up, repelling the second attack and allowing a line of attack into Partion while also granting the Helldivers victory in their operation.\nOperation Alcubierre-II.\nHowever, the colonists at Phact Bay were unable to enjoy their recently gained freedom. Less than a couple weeks after the re-liberation of their planet, the Terminids at Partion sent an attack onto Phact Bay. After holding out for 2 days with what little defenses they could arrange, Phact Bay fell to Terminid control on September 28th. Then, a day later, the Terminids went on to sent an assault from Phact Bay to Darius II by forcefully creating new FTL Supply Lines into the planet.\nOperation Adamant Resolve.\nPhact Bay would remain under Terminid control for a whole month, mainly due to other operations taking priority over Phact Bay's liberation. However, slowly but surely, progress would be made, as the Helldivers would dive into Phact Bay whenever no objectives needed to be progressed. A bulk of the progress towards Phact Bay's liberation would be made during Liberty Day, with the only thing stopping it being the defense of Gatria nearby.\nBy October 29th, after an entire month of horrendous attrition, Phact Bay would be finally liberated, just in time to allow the Helldivers back into Pandion-XXIV and allowing them to continue with the major order's objectives.\nOperation Bughammer.\nPhact Bay would remain free of Terminid control ever since its liberation on October 29th. However, it would not remain free of the ever-present threat of the Terminid Horde. Following the disaster at the Terminid Research Preserve on November 12th, Pandion-XXIV would fall immediately to the Terminids, leaving Phact Bay exposed to further attacks.\nThis threat would build up slowly over the remainder of the month until, on December 11th, Phact Bay would be attacked from both Pandion and Partion, as the Terminids began offensive in the midst of new construction projects taking place at &lt;a href=\"Achernar%20Secundus\"&gt;Achernar Secundus&lt;/a&gt;. With Phact Bay having such a direct route towards a project of such importance, the Helldivers deployed en masse, hoping to form a security belt around Achernar in hopes of preventing any and all interruptions to the multi-trillion Super Credit venture between AM Defense and the government of Super Earth."}
