{"id": "3832", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3832", "title": "Points of Interest", "text": "In Helldivers 2, Points of Interest are scattered around the area of operation. The amount that can be found varies. Points of Interest can be sought out in multiple ways:\nSpecial Loot.\nMost Points of Interest feature a special loot vessel. A Pod has space for 1, a Container has space for 2, and a Bunker has space for 3 with possible additional Supplies inside.\nSpecial Loot may be one of the following:\nAn undocumented Rare Sample is a sample that doesn't count towards the sample limit counter located on the top right corner during a mission.\nTypes.\nThere are various types of Points of Interest.\nGround Stash.\nThis small Point of Interest can spawn from difficulty 1 onward, and is noticeable from a distance due to a lamp shining across an open panel in the ground.\nVariations:\nDamaged Hellbomb.\nThis small Point of Interest is a sparking and smoking Hellbomb with an inscription scribbled onto it. The hellbomb explodes shortly after damaging it with anything.\nInscriptions, called \"Words scribbled on Bomb\":\nVariations:\nGraves.\nThis small Point of Interest features 2 headstones, 1 human corpse and 1 Terminid corpse. Sometimes the human had a Break-Action Shotgun, sometimes they killed the Terminid with their shovel. It can also have supplies and samples.\nSilvery Rock.\nThis medium Point of Interest features a rock shaped like a chicken drumstick and has silvery veins running across it.\nVariations:\nUnderground Container.\nThis medium Point of Interest features a container below ground with some supplies and samples scattered around. It also has a readable note with variations in its content:\nIt also has a larger variation, an Entrenchment, which features a lot of supplies, some samples and sometimes even a &lt;a href=\"E/MG-101%20HMG%20Emplacement\"&gt;E/MG-101 HMG Emplacement&lt;/a&gt;\nL-shaped House.\nThis medium Point of Interest features an L-Shaped House with some supplies and samples.\nVariations:\nElevated House.\nThis medium Point of Interest features an elevated House with some supplies and samples.\nVariations:\nFarm.\nThis medium Point of Interest features a small to medium size farm with supplies and samples.\nVariations:\nBunker.\nThis medium Point of Interest features a Bunker door, which can only be opened by two Helldivers pressing each button at the same time. It may have supplies and samples outside, but inside it additionally contains special loot. Rare Samples, &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Super%20Credits\"&gt;Super Credits&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Requisition%20Slips\"&gt;Requisition Slip&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;Medals&lt;/a&gt; inside the bunker are not generated until the door has been opened.\nVariations:\nCrashed Ship.\nThis medium Point of Interest features a crashed Pelican dropship with an outcrop next to it. The outcrop sometimes has supplies and 2 explosive barrels. The wake of the crashed ship has 0-2 common samples and 0-1 grenade cases. There's also a Captain's Log with the message \"Transporting a large shipment of flamethrowers. Heavy enemy presence - delivery expected to take the whole day. Derek forgot the fire extinguisher but I'm sure we'll be fi-\"\nVariations:\nE-710 Spill.\nThis medium Point of Interest features the wreck of a large vessel, often fenced off, with small fires and pools of E-710 within. Supplies and Samples are often found within.\nCity Wall.\nCertain points along a city wall will have some sort of opening, allowing Helldivers to pass through without needing a &lt;a href=\"Backpacks%23Jump%20Pack\"&gt;Jump Pack&lt;/a&gt;, Hellpod, or HE ordnance. These openings are often large enough for &lt;a href=\"vehicles\"&gt;vehicles&lt;/a&gt; to pass through. There generally are no loot containers.\nVariations:\nCity Cache.\nIn city bounds, supplies and samples may be gathered at strategic points. There generally are no loot containers. (Note that supplies and support weapons may also be found at non-PoI caches.)\nVariations:"}
