{"id": "4889", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4889", "title": "Pump Fuel to ICBM", "text": "Pump Fuel to ICBM is a rather easy mission, as it's only ever found as a primary objective on Trivial and Easy difficulties; while also found as a sub-objective on higher difficulties of the &lt;a href=\"Launch%20ICBM\"&gt;Launch ICBM&lt;/a&gt; mission. \nGameplay.\n&lt;br&gt;\nAs with most objectives, the Helldiver must activate a local terminal and press the prompted directional inputs to begin the process of reactivating the fueling station. After the terminal has been activated properly the Helldiver must use the on-screen prompts to reallocate the fuel lines from the Local Storage to the Missile Silo. After the fuel lines have been properly aligned, the Helldiver must go to three separate pump valves and turn them to open the fuel lines. Once this has been completed, the terminal requires one more directional input to activate the pumps and complete the objective."}
{"id": "5505", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5505", "title": "Purge Hatcheries", "text": ""}
{"id": "3463", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3463", "title": "P\u00f6pli IX", "text": "P\u00f6pli IX is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Xzar%20Sector\"&gt;Xzar Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Expeditions.\nP\u00f6pli IX had spent many years as a peaceful, sand-blasted mining colony of Super Earth, its colonists toiling happily as they enjoyed the tender, benevolent rule of Managed Democracy. However, in the depths of space, a new foe rallied and nurtured its strength.\nIn the first week of March 2184, the Automatons, heartless killing machines driven by socialism and hatred for the ways of Freedom, launched a surprise attack upon the innocent colonies in the Xzar and &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin&lt;/a&gt; Sectors. Against its will, P\u00f6pli IX, and neighboring Ingmar with it, had been plunged head first into the Second Galactic War, shortly after the fall of Mantes a week prior.\nFrom March to April, P\u00f6pli IX would endure the horrors brought upon itself by the invading bots, barely receiving any Helldiver support (in comparison to planets like &lt;a href=\"Tibit\"&gt;Tibit&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; during the same time period)\nHowever, shortly after the siege of &lt;a href=\"Tien%20Kwan\"&gt;Tien Kwan&lt;/a&gt;, P\u00f6pli IX's opportunity to return to Liberty would arise.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nOperation Swift Disassembly would be greenlit by Super Earth High Command on the last week of March. The first step was to liberate &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt; in order to destroy an important Automaton Communications Array. On the way to Troost, parts of the Helldiver corps would deviate towards Draupnir in order to conduct secondary liberation campaigns on the Xzar Sector. P\u00f6pli IX would be liberated on March 29th, shortly before the Automatons were decisively defeated on &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt; on April 3rd, restoring peace on the planet\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nFrom April onwards, P\u00f6pli IX has remained free alongside with the rest of the Xzar Sector. But it did not regain the peace it had been robbed off as, a mere 2 days after their defeat on Malevelon Creek, the Automatons launched a second invasion upon Super Earth Territory, now targetting &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt; and all surrounding sectors.\nP\u00f6pli IX's colonists would conduct the repairs on their sufficiently-sized homes with dread on their minds as the days passed and they watched the Automatons approaching the Xzar Sector one planet at a time.\nOn April 25th, P\u00f6pli IX would be given a fright as the Automatons launched their first assault on Mort. This assault would fail miserably, showing how vastly overstretched the robotic colonizers were amidst their constant usurpations.\nOn late May, Mort would take a second assault, the Automatons committing more forces than in their first attempt yet, as expected from all who oppose the unquestionable rule of Freedom, failed once more.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nUp until June, P\u00f6pli IX stood on high alert as, while Mort had been defended in two occasions, the Automatons had hunkered down on &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt; in the neighboring &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda Sector&lt;/a&gt; up north, using it as a forward base on which to concentrate their forces. Then, on June 21st, a third Automaton assault took over Mort while the Helldivers were occupied with the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; Front. Super Earth would issue a new Major Order. P\u00f6pli IX and the rest of the Xzar Sector had to be defended from the Automatons.\nOn June 22nd, the Automatons on Mort would make a move to attempt a takeover of Ingmar but would be repealed. Then, on June 24th, they would launch 2 parallel assaults. One would go from recently captured Vandalon IV to Ingmar and the other went from Mort to P\u00f6pli IX. The Helldivers, in a textbook display of military prowess, would successfully defend Ingmar and defeat the invasion force on Mort, which would cripple the assault on P\u00f6pli to a halt, giving Super Earth a peerless victory.\nHowever, P\u00f6pli would not get to regain its lost peace. On June 24th, the Automatons made an unprecedented move. They would launch an assault onto Mantes through a new FTL Line they would create from Vandalon IV. Despite the successful defense on Mantes, this left P\u00f6pli IX with a new fear: That one day, an Automaton Fleet may appear out of nowhere to occupy it once more."}
{"id": "3307", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3307", "title": "Quintus Sector", "text": "The Quintus Sector is a sector found in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of 5 planets."}
{"id": "6930", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6930", "title": "R-2124 Constitution", "text": "The R-2124 Constitution is a bolt-action rifle given to all citizens of Super Earth on their 16th birthday.\nIt was authorized for deployment on Helldiver Corps missions on &lt;a href=\"Liberty%20Day\"&gt;Liberty Day&lt;/a&gt; 2184 (October 26), in standard black/yellow livery, and fitted with a standard bayonet.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Constitution fills an unusual niche, being a marksman rifle with improved melee combat capability.\nThe rifle's performance generally suffers from its low magazine capacity and lack of optics, despite damage falling between the &lt;a href=\"R-63%20Diligence\"&gt;R-63 Diligence&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"R-63CS%20Diligence%20Counter%20Sniper\"&gt;R-63CS Diligence Counter Sniper&lt;/a&gt;. While it carries a comparable load of ammunition, it is strictly a per-round reload, with no stripper clips available to quickly top off. It also lacks optics and attachments available to other weapons, limiting ability to acquire targets.\nThe mounted bayonet replaces the buttstock strike used as a melee attack with other primary weapons. The Constitution gives Helldivers some well-appreciated standoff in close combat, with no stamina drain.\nBoth the rifle round and bayonet provides Medium (3) armor penetration, with comparable durable damage (50 per round, 55 per thrust).\nOverall, the Diligence variants remain superior options except when challenging oneself to melee combat."}
{"id": "4310", "revid": "56038594", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4310", "title": "R-36 Eruptor", "text": "The R-36 Eruptor is an Explosive Weapon utilized in Helldivers 2 unlocked in the second page of &lt;a href=\"Democratic%20Detonation\"&gt;Warbond: Democratic Detonation&lt;/a&gt;.. The R-36 is a unique marksman's weapon that fire a highly-accurate, two-stage jet-propelled rounds, similar to the &lt;a href=\"JAR-5%20Dominator\"&gt;JAR-5 Dominator&lt;/a&gt;. However, these rounds are larger, and have a powerful explosive payload. \nDue to the unique load, the gun is a bolt-action rifle, requiring the user to manually chamber a round after every shot.\nDuring the first war, some early batches of Eruptor ammo were found to have an unwieldy amount of Orbital Airburst Strike shrapnel. Producing damage that officials categorized as \"unbalanced\", stocks were pulled from theater to study the absurd potential of the ammunition. Succeeding batches have proven rather disappointing due to shrapnel shortages, but manufacturers seek to reproduce even a fraction of their former power. During the second war, Eruptor ammo has been modified once again to add fragmentation shrapnel, making it still quite devastating, but more survivable for its users compared to its original ammunition.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe R-36 is an anti-materiel rifle. It fires powerful fragmentation round that deal significant damage in an area and also have limited anti-structure capabilities.\nHowever, it is very ill-suited for close quarters combat as its explosive, fragmentation rounds have a wide AoE, and is very likely to kill its user, just as much as the enemy, at these ranges.\nThe weapon is high-risk, high-reward. While its power will allow one to decimate a good chunk of the enemy roster on both sides, it is a bolt-action rifle, and so there is a delay between follow-up shots. This makes misses very punishing, especially in tense situations.\nThe Eruptor excels at destroying bug holes and fabricators, and can also clear light objectives such as &lt;a href=\"Terminate%20Illegal%20Broadcast\"&gt;illegal broadcasts&lt;/a&gt; and enemy transmission towers."}
{"id": "3784", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3784", "title": "R-63CS Diligence Counter Sniper", "text": " \nThe R-63CS Diligence Counter Sniper is the modified version of the &lt;a href=\"R-63%20Diligence\"&gt;R-63 Diligence&lt;/a&gt; featuring a higher damage output in exchange for reduced ammo capacity and greater recoil. It also features an longer-range scope allowing for further engagements. \nIt is unlocked upon reaching the seventh page of the standard war bonds. \n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nMost of the advice for using the R-63CS carries over from the R-63. It is recommended divers carry a decent sidearm for close quarters fighting and they go against enemies who fight at range. The upgraded scope allows the marksman to engage at further ranges with the higher damage output reducing the total shots needed to take down an enemy. It is highly encouraged to prioritize enemies attempting to call in reinforcements, as a single shot to these enemies can save a lot of stress in more difficult missions.\nAnother major difference NOT listed on the stats between the R-63 and R-63CS is the \"drag\" of the scope. The R-63CS, much like the Anti-Materiel Rifle, has scope \"drag,\" where moving your scope around quickly requires you to wait a brief moment before the scope is actually aligned with your target. The R-63's \"drag\" is almost nonexistent and allows for quick consecutive shots from target to target, but with the RC-63CS this is much harder to pull off.\nA recommended loadout is to carry an explosive anti-vehicle weapon, like the &lt;a href=\"GR-8%20Recoilless%20Rifle\"&gt;GR-8 Recoilless Rifle&lt;/a&gt; or the &lt;a href=\"FAF-14%20Spear\"&gt;FAF-14 Spear&lt;/a&gt;. This is due to the fact that the marksman will be far enough away to safely reload the weapon solo and it allows them to reliably support squad mates further up.\nUpdates.\nPatch &lt;a href=\"Updates%20%26amp%3B%20Patch%20Notes%23April%202nd%202024\"&gt;01.000.200&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;br&gt;\n \u2045 Increased Armor Penetration from Light Penetration to Medium Penetration."}
{"id": "3781", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3781", "title": "R-63 Diligence", "text": " \nThe R-63 Diligence is the standard marksman rifle in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" Filling the primary weapon slot, it is a light armor penetrating weapon which excels at engaging enemies at range. \nIt is unlocked upon reaching the second page of the standard war bonds. A modified variant of this weapon, the &lt;a href=\"R-63CS%20Diligence%20Counter%20Sniper\"&gt;R-63CS Diligence Counter Sniper&lt;/a&gt;, is available on page seven. \n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe R-63 is primarily a weapon for engaging enemies at a distance with precise fire. For this reason it is mostly useful against Automatons who mostly use ranged weapons. While it can be fired from the hip the low rate of fire and ammo capacity make it ill suited for this role. It is recommended to pair it up with a decent side arm for a diver to switch to when fighting in close quarters. It is also recommended any marksman using this find decent cover as enemies tend to know where everyone in a squad is the moment fighting starts."}
