{"id": "3415", "revid": "26489601", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3415", "title": "RS-422 Railgun", "text": "The RS-422 Railgun is one of the &lt;a href=\"stratagems\"&gt;stratagems&lt;/a&gt; available to the player in Helldivers 2, unlocked at Level 20. \nIt is a single-shot marksman's weapon that uses high-powered magnets to fire a single ferro-magnetic projectile that can penetrate tank-level armor. The weapon must be charged up before firing, which can be done in safe or unsafe mode. Charges in safe mode can be held indefinitely, while charges in unsafe mode will cause the weapon to explode if held too long.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:\nStrategy.\nUpdates.\nPatch 01.000.100: &lt;br&gt;\n \u25ba Decreased armor penetration in Safe Mode, decreased damage against durable enemy parts \nPatch 01.000.300: \n \u25ba Increased armor penetration in both safe mode and unsafe mode \u25ba Stagger force slightly reduced\nPatch 01.001.100:\n \u25ba Durable damage increased from 60 to 225 \u25ba Fully overcharging damage increased from 150% to 250%\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "6843", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6843", "title": "Radar Station", "text": "A SEAF Radar Station provides useful information about the surrounding area, and can often be found during missions as a &lt;a href=\"Objectives%23Tactical%20Objectives\"&gt;Optional Objective&lt;/a&gt;.\nAppearance.\nRadar Stations can often be located from a distance by their tower mast with stowed radar dish.\nSome common layouts:\nOperation.\nAfter data is uploaded to the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;, the squad on ground gains map updates on all previously hidden locations, including &lt;a href=\"Points%20of%20Interest\"&gt;Points of Interest&lt;/a&gt; and objectives such as &lt;a href=\"Stalker%20Lair\"&gt;Stalker Lair&lt;/a&gt;s and &lt;a href=\"Gunship%20Facility\"&gt;Gunship Facilities&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3557", "revid": "47694645", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3557", "title": "Ranks", "text": "Ranks are titles displayed next to your level on your player tag, they are earned through leveling and can be equipped in customizations like armor pieces.\nYour Rank (or \"Level\" as it is in-game), like the , is a measure of a Helldiver's experience in the field. After gaining the required amount of experience from completing missions across the galaxy, a Helldiver will advance in rank, possibly unlocking new Ship Modules, Stratagem permits and titles. Experience is gained after missions based on difficulty and overall outcome. Each completed objective will reward some experience, killing enemies does not factor in by itself.\nHowever, unlike the first game, titles are only unlocked after every 5 levels until reaching rank 50, where they continue to unlock every 10 levels. New titles do not automatically apply as levels are gained, but any rank can be chosen to display in the armory once unlocked."}
