{"id": "3828", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3828", "title": "Retrieve Essential Personnel", "text": "Its chaos down there, helldiver! The enemy is attempting to gain control over one of our planets. In doing so, some essential scientists have been put in danger. This must not be tolerated. As such, we are tasking you with an important mission. You must dive on the place the civilians are trapped and ready the evacuation shuttle. Then open the bunker doors and protect the civilians as they escape. To keep things orderly, only three civilians will be allowed to exit at a time. Once the shuttle is full, we will send down an extraction beacon. Remember: there are more citizens trapped than can fit in the shuttle. As such, it shouldn't be too much of an issue if one or two unfortunate accidents occur."}
{"id": "6858", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6858", "title": "Retrieve Recon Craft Intel", "text": "A Retrieve Recon Craft Intel mission tasks Helldivers with recovering the sensitive intelligence data from crashed reconnaissance aircraft (that are certainly not spying on our own citizens). It resembles the &lt;a href=\"Retrieve%20Valuable%20Data\"&gt;Retrieve Valuable Data&lt;/a&gt; mission, with the main exception of the large crash site that must be explored.\nGameplay.\nSecure Black Box.\nThe &lt;a href=\"Package\"&gt;Black Box&lt;/a&gt;\u2014a hardened storage device containing an aircraft's self-reported and collected data\u2014from the recon craft can be found somewhere in the vicinity of its crash site, spanning several city blocks. To assist location, the black box emits visual and audible beacons until picked up or delivered. Once picked up, the sub-objective is complete. (Note that this differs from Retrieve Valuable Data where the SSSD must be delivered to the receptacle before completion is credited.)\nThe crash site will typically be occupied by &lt;a href=\"Voteless\"&gt;Voteless&lt;/a&gt; and their captors. All must be prosecuted for illegal trespassing and loitering near Ministry of Defense assets.\nUpload Black Box Data.\nAt the nearest Local Relay, Helldivers must deliver the Black Box to the receptacle and activate the Terminal. The relay's Satellite Tower must then be raised. With the satellite dish assembled, transmission of the data must be initiated by steering the satellite dish and confirming position at the terminal. At this point, the terminal can be left unattended as it performs handshake protocols with the Super Earth Mainframe and proceeds with upload. The mission is complete when the data upload is finished. (Note again that the Black Box does not need to be securely wiped, unlike other SSSDs.)"}
{"id": "4910", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4910", "title": "Retrieve Valuable Data", "text": "The Retrieve Valuable Data mission tasks Helldivers with collecting important research and operational data from overrun colonies and re-integrating it with the Super Earth galaxy-wide network.\nIt is always guaranteed to have minimum of 2 steps, with a third step added on higher difficulties. These steps go by: Collect Encrypted Hard Drive and Reactivate Power Relay (Sub-objectives that can be done in any order), and Upload Data via Local Relay (primary objective that can only be completed once all sub-objectives are complete).\nEach of the objective sites generally carries a small number of &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Samples\"&gt;Common Samples&lt;/a&gt;, and a few Rare Samples at Challenging (4) difficulty and higher.\nGameplay.\nCollect Encrypted Hard Drive.\nThis sub-objective is guaranteed in every mission and requires the Helldiver to go to a small research outpost, download the research to an SSSD, and carry the container to the Local Relay for upload. To reiterate, this case must be manually carried by a Helldiver to the final objective and is mandatory to complete it. On higher difficulty missions, there may be multiple SSSDs to retrieve.\nHelldivers are unable to use most primary weapons, support weapons, stratagems, or emotes while carrying the SSSD, and will instead drop the SSSD at its current location. The carrier is otherwise limited to one-handed weapons such as SMGs (with notable exception of the &lt;a href=\"SMG-32%20Reprimand\"&gt;SMG-32 Reprimand&lt;/a&gt;), sidearms, and &lt;a href=\"throwables\"&gt;throwables&lt;/a&gt;; and &lt;a href=\"Backpacks\"&gt;Backpacks&lt;/a&gt;.\nAgain, note that the objective is not considered complete until the loaded SSSD is brought all the way to the Local Relay site. To assist the squad, the SSSD will be marked on the minimap with a Package (briefcase) icon, and the site where the data was originally stored will be grayed.\nReactivate Power Relay.\nOn Suicide Mission (7) and higher the Power Relay sub-objective will be required to complete to finish the primary objective; the power will always be active on lower difficulties. (If the Helldiver goes to the final objective before reactivating the generator, they can activate the initial terminal but cannot progress as it states \"Error - No Power\" on its screen.) To reactivate the Power Relay, the Helldiver must log in to the terminal via directional inputs then wait for it to perform a system diagnostics check. Once completed, it will find 5 blown fuses that must be reset individually at the terminal. Once they've all been reset, the voltage must be calibrated to maximize the output via a signal strength adjustment. After which the Helldiver must wait a short moment before they can flip the switch on the generator and complete the sub-objective.\nUpload Data via Local Relay.\nOnce the Power Relay is online if on higher difficulties and the SSSD has been carried to the Local Relay location, the Helldiver can work on completing the primary objective. To begin, the Helldiver must login to the terminal via directional code and begin raising the Satellite Tower. Once fully raised, it will have to be manually aligned using the wheel at the base of the tower to match the alignment position that displays on the terminal. Once aligned, the Helldiver must wait approximately 40 seconds for the data transfer to complete, after which they'll be required to wipe all sensitive data and be considered mission accomplished.\nThe Local Relay site often consists of two rock formations, the larger carrying the Satellite Tower, some ammunition, and occasionally a Support Weapon, and a power transformer unit near the end of its slope. The smaller formation (often separated by shallow water) has the Terminal and various objects that provide temporary cover."}
{"id": "3312", "revid": "55287310", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3312", "title": "Rictus Sector", "text": "The Rictus Sector is an inhabited area on the &lt;a href=\"Southern%20Front\"&gt;Southern Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Located on galactic south from &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, it consists of 7 colonized systems.\nTogether with rest of sectors in Federation's south, it came under attack in middle of December, 2184, by once thought extinct . Mostly compromised of small raiding fleets, it seems their main goal is abduction of as many citizen as possible."}
