{"id": "6387", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6387", "title": "SEAF", "text": ""}
{"id": "3688", "revid": "26489601", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3688", "title": "SEAF Artillery", "text": "S.E.A.F Artillery Cannon.\nThe S.E.A.F (&lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Armed%20Forces\"&gt;Super Earth Armed Forces&lt;/a&gt;) artillery cannon is a large emplacement which can hold a total of five S.E.A.F shells of varying types. There may only be one S.E.A.F artillery position on a single mission at once. \nS.E.A.F shells of varying types will spawn in several locations throughout a S.E.A.F fortification. There will always be at least 5 shells present but spawn-rates tend towards 7-8 shells.\nOnce five shells are loaded into the S.E.A.F artillery cannon and it is connected to the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;: the Helldivers gain a new &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;stratagem&lt;/a&gt; which they can use to fire one round from the S.E.A.F cannon towards a designated position.\nThe cannon fires the shells in the order in which they were placed; where the first shell loaded is the first shell fired and so on.\nThe cannon cannot be restocked with new shells after it is activated.\nMission Brief.\nHelldivers, you are the shock troops of Managed Democracy when all else fails. But you are not the first. The ones who came before you and fell in the defense of liberty were the Super Earth Armed Forces Troopers (SEAF). They used these artillery installation to shout the praises of Managed Democracy before they fell silent against the onslaught. You get to make the very ground shudder with their songs again!\nWhen you encounter the artillery installation you first must activate the terminal so it can begin to compose its symphony of liberty once again. Lying around you will be shells that will be the notes of your anthem to load into the battery itself. Pay attention as each shell will have a different effect and the order in which you load them will affect the order in which you have access to them. These shell may create an explosive, nuke, ems, or smoke effect. You will always find at least 5 in the vicinity and at times there may be more. This objective does tend to draw enemies like an extraction point. Be wary of their presence and prepare accordingly.\nNot only does this objective give you mission rewards, but your team now unlocks a new stratagem! You will have 5 shared charges with a low cooldown between your group. Each charge will cause the artillery instillation to dispense your pre-loaded choice of managed democracy on whomever you will...friends included.\nGameplay Tactics.\nA S.E.A.F artillery position can be seen on the map - when in detectable range - by a blinking question mark (also note the circular crater which can be used to spot these positions): "}
{"id": "5099", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5099", "title": "SEAF SAM Site", "text": "SEAF Sam-Site.\nThe SEAF SAM Site is a sub-objective found in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt; in planets occupied by both the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt;. \nThe objective is located in an abandoned SEAF firebase with an inactive surface-to-air missile launcher. The launcher can be brought back in operational status by using the terminal nearby and configuring it back into service.\nOnce re-activated, the SAM site will automatically target nearby &lt;a href=\"Dropship\"&gt;Dropship&lt;/a&gt;s, &lt;a href=\"Gunship\"&gt;Gunship&lt;/a&gt;s, or &lt;a href=\"Warp%20Ship\"&gt;Warp Ship&lt;/a&gt;s with guided surface-to-air-missiles for the remainder of the mission, serving as area-denial support for Helldivers. Note that while targeting systems are close to map-wide, the missiles only have a limited range of perhaps 350 meters."}
{"id": "6555", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6555", "title": "SG-20 Halt", "text": " \nThe SG-20 Halt appears in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;\" as a semi-automatic variant of the &lt;a href=\"SG-8%20Punisher\"&gt;SG-8 Punisher&lt;/a&gt;. The weapon is notable for being the first, and so far only, weapon to make use of it's dual magazine system to use \"humane\" (relatively) non-lethal stun rounds, and lethal armor-piercing flechette rounds.\nIt can be unlocked on the first page of the &lt;a href=\"Truth%20Enforcers\"&gt;Truth Enforcers&lt;/a&gt; Warbond.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Halt offers utility similar to that of the &lt;a href=\"SMG-72%20Pummeler\"&gt;SMG-72 Pummeler&lt;/a&gt; in suppressing small crowds of dissidents and/or larger threats to democratic well-being. It can also function as a medium-hitting shotgun similar to the &lt;a href=\"SG-8S%20Slugger\"&gt;SG-8S Slugger&lt;/a&gt;. Isolated targets can be effectively silenced and disposed, while larger groups require more coordination to successfully control."}
{"id": "4416", "revid": "56289", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4416", "title": "SG-225IE Breaker Incendiary", "text": "The SG-225IE Breaker Incendiary is a burst-fire, drum magazine-fed shotgun in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" A modified version of the &lt;a href=\"SG-225%20Breaker\"&gt;SG-225 Breaker&lt;/a&gt;, the Incendiary version is outfitted with a drum magazine giving it a larger ammo capacity compared to the standard weapon. It fires Incendiary buckshot that sets targets ablaze, burning them overtime in addition to tearing them to shreds.\nIt can be unlocked on page two of the &lt;a href=\"Steeled%20Veterans\"&gt;Warbond: Steeled Veterans&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Breaker Incendiary is an excellent weapon against groups of small and unarmored targets, such as the Scavengers and Warriors among the Terminids, or the Troopers among the Automatons. With its large magazine, its capable of delivering a large volume of fire in addition to setting targets ablaze to burn them overtime. Unlike most shotguns and its fellow Breakers, the Incendiary lacks any sort of stopping power, making it unable to stagger targets. It makes up for this in its ability to bypass armor and set targets on fire, burning them overtime. However, one shouldn't rely on its ability to burn targets to take out heavier opponents, as the burning may vary depending on how large the enemy is.\nAgainst armored targets, the Incendiary, while capable of bypassing the armor with fire, will have its projectiles richote off the armor. It's recommended when using the Breaker Incendiary to target weak spots against enemies to deliver maximum damage."}
{"id": "3778", "revid": "57559", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3778", "title": "SG-225SP Breaker Spray&amp;Pray", "text": "The SG-225SP Breaker Spray&amp;Pray is an automatic, drum magazine-fed shotgun in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" A modified version of the &lt;a href=\"SG-225%20Breaker\"&gt;SG-225 Breaker&lt;/a&gt;, the Spray&amp;Pray version is outfitted with a drum magazine to give it a much larger ammo capacity than the standard Breaker, along with a duckbill muzzle, making its spread very horizontal but less vertical. Instead of being loaded with buckshot or slugs, it is loaded with birdshot which increases the odds of scoring a hit in exchange for lesser penetration and per pellet damage.\nIt can be unlocked on page nine of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Breaker SP is an extremely useful weapon against smaller unarmored targets like &lt;a href=\"Scavenger\"&gt;Scavenger&lt;/a&gt;s and low level &lt;a href=\"Warrior\"&gt;Warrior&lt;/a&gt; bugs as it can decimate large numbers of these enemies. With the emergence of the Shriekers this weapon has become even more valuable. Its rapid rate of fire combined with a high number of pellets means it can obliterate these flying pests with ease. \nIt will however struggle against medium or heavy armored enemies unless a weak point is hit. This will often mean their utility against Automatons is much lower than against Terminids."}
{"id": "3760", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3760", "title": "SG-225 Breaker", "text": " \nThe SG-225 Breaker is an automatic, box magazine-fed shotgun in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" A potent weapon that packs a considerable punch at close to medium range with a relatively fast fire rate compared to other shotguns, the Breaker is nevertheless plagued by a limited ammo capacity that makes it dependent on frequent resupply, and suffers at extended ranges due to spread and high recoil. In spite of these shortcomings, however, the Breaker has solidified itself as a go-to primary weapon for many &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt can be unlocked on page four of Warbond: &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt;. Two variants of the weapon, the &lt;a href=\"SG-225SP%20Breaker%20Spray%26amp%3BPray\"&gt;SG-225SP Breaker Spray&amp;Pray&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"SG-225IE%20Breaker%20Incendiary\"&gt;SG-225IE Breaker Incendiary&lt;/a&gt;, are also available. \n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Breaker is a great all-around weapon for dealing with most commonly encountered enemies, being able to clear groups of lightly-armored enemies at close range by unleashing a flurry of automatic fire, while also being able to accurately target enemies at moderate distance or weak points on more heavily-armored foes by tap-firing or by firing in semi-automatic. Ammo capacity is its primary limitation, and efforts should be made to conserve ammo at all times; for dealing with individual fodder enemies you may want to consider switching to your secondary or engaging them in melee, and you should be particularly considerate of when you do or do not perform tactical reloads."}
{"id": "5530", "revid": "57561", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5530", "title": "SG-22 Bushwhacker", "text": "The SG-22 Bushwhacker is a triple-barreled, break-action sawed-off shotgun sidearm.\nIt appears to be a common civilian break-action shotgun, with the barrel and stock sawn-off to give it a pistol's profile, then given a custom handguard to give it a front sight, side-mounted shell rack, and a thicker profile to make it easier to hold.\nIt holds three shells and features a firing mode to shoot all loaded shells at once. Promising extreme damage at the cost of ammunition economy with it only having 33 total shells if you count the three shells that are loaded this yielding a total damage of 13365 if you hit every shot. \nThe low ammo count also means that the triple barrel firing mode, while dishing out a massive 1215 damage shot can only be used eleven times before you are out of ammo. This renders the triple barrel firing mode more or less reserved for calculated shots to weak spots such as heatsinks or other high priority targets like &lt;a href=\"Stalker\"&gt;Stalkers&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe SG-22 is overall a very capable sidearm and while being a shotgun is still accurate up to 50 meters with a single shell and can stay effective up to 80 meters with the triple barrel firing mode. It is especially useful for dealing with stronger targets such as &lt;a href=\"Hulk\"&gt;Hulks&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt;s where the triple shot can be used to deal quick massive damage."}
{"id": "5093", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5093", "title": "SG-88 Break-Action Shotgun", "text": "The SG-88 Break-Action Shotgun is a support weapon that can be found at points of interest on any planet on any difficulty. It is a standard over-under shotgun, fitted with a futuristic stock.\nIt is generally found on the corpses of civilians and SEAF personnel who made a heroic last stand."}
{"id": "5078", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5078", "title": "SG-8P Punisher Plasma", "text": "The SG-8P Punisher Plasma is a unique energy weapon that utilizes cartridges much like the &lt;a href=\"PLAS-1%20Scorcher\"&gt;PLAS-1 Scorcher&lt;/a&gt;. Unlike the other Punisher variants, it functions more like a Grenade launcher. It shoots large, slow projectiles that travel in an arc and explode on impact that stagger enemies and penetrate armor. It can make quick work of smaller enemies and groups, but the user must account for the weapons arcing projectiles.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role:&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Punisher Plasma is a rapid-fire bombardment weapon, most effective in medium to long range. Its projectiles travel in an arch, allowing the user to carpet entire areas in explosions. The weapon pairs will with gun sentries thanks to its ability to stagger, and its long range allow the shooter to assist teammates being attacked by enemies.\nIt is akin to a side grade to the &lt;a href=\"PLAS-1%20Scorcher\"&gt;PLAS-1 Scorcher&lt;/a&gt; where it sacrifices fire rate and projectile speed for more damage and ability to stagger.\nHistory.\n1.000.302\n1.000.300"}
{"id": "3762", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3762", "title": "SG-8S Slugger", "text": " \nThe SG-8 Slugger is a pump-action, dual tube-fed shotgun in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;.\" As a modified version of the base &lt;a href=\"SG-8%20Punisher\"&gt;SG-8 Punisher&lt;/a&gt; it trades buckshot rounds for slug rounds.\nThe Slugger is available on page eight of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt;. \n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Slugger trades crowd control for instead heavy damage to a single target. Primarily useful against larger unarmored enemies like &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commanders&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Stalker\"&gt;Stalker&lt;/a&gt;s. Much like the base model Punisher, the wielder can only carry 60 rounds, plus 16 rounds in the gun itself, making it not a very good choice for dispatching waves of fodder enemies. \nWhile it is recommended to still aim for weak points as despite being able to penetrate medium armor, it will still inflict reduced damage."}
{"id": "5655", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5655", "title": "SG-8 Punisher", "text": " \nSG-8 Punisher Shotgun \nThe SG-8 Punisher is a pump-action, dual tube-fed shotgun featured in \"&lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;\". As one of the first unlockable weapons, the Punisher delivers powerful shots with high damage per round and offers a relatively high ammunition capacity. It excels at dispatching lightly-armored enemies quickly, though it suffers from damage falloff due to shot spread and a slower rate of fire inherent to its pump-action mechanism.\nAvailability\nThe Punisher can be unlocked on the first page of the Warbond: &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt; section for 4 Medals.\nVariants include:\nRole and Performance\nThe Punisher is highly effective against lightly-armored enemies at close range. However, its slower fire rate can be a drawback when dealing with large groups of weaker enemies. Additionally, the Punisher can stagger enemies on a successful hit, preventing larger Terminids from initiating a bug breach. This makes the Punisher a valuable early-game counter against threats like &lt;a href=\"Stalker\"&gt;Stalkers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastators&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Brood%20Commander\"&gt;Brood Commanders&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Hive%20Guard\"&gt;Hive Guards&lt;/a&gt;."}
