{"id": "4114", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4114", "title": "SMG-37 Defender", "text": "The SMG-37 Defender is a side-loaded open bolt submachine gun unlocked early on and is the most viable one-handed weapon for all combat situations. It is equipped with a reflex red dot and a flashlight laser combo.\nThe weapon can be found on the 2nd page of the Warbond: &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%20Mobilize\"&gt;Helldivers Mobilize&lt;/a&gt; for 15 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;Medals&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nThe Defender is the most versatile weapon to use while carrying a Hard Drive or wielding a &lt;a href=\"Backpacks%23Ballistic%20Shield\"&gt;Ballistic Shield&lt;/a&gt;. The SMG is very lightweight and the one-handed trait allows you to shoot over your shoulder without a movement penalty if a tactical reposition is necessary. Boasting a high damage and lower rate of fire allows the Defender to engage from close to medium range, eliminating &lt;a href=\"Scavenger\"&gt;Scavengers&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Commissar\"&gt;Commissars&lt;/a&gt; with one shot while being able to place accurate headshots to a &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastator&lt;/a&gt; from a safe distance."}
{"id": "4808", "revid": "1348475", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4808", "title": "SMG-72 Pummeler", "text": "The SMG-72 Pummeler is a submachinegun identical to the &lt;a href=\"SMG-37%20Defender\"&gt;SMG-37 Defender&lt;/a&gt;, it has lower fire rate and damage but can stagger enemies. The concussive nature of the rounds works different from those fired from the &lt;a href=\"AR-23C%20Liberator%20Concussive\"&gt;AR-23C Liberator Concussive&lt;/a&gt; where the stun is treated as a status effect that can temporality incapacitate enemies and be lengthened with sustained fire. \nThe Pummeler makes light work of small and medium threats as enemies shot by sustained fire are rendered helpless due to the high stagger. \n&lt;a href=\"Know%20Your%20Role\"&gt;Role&lt;/a&gt;:.\nDue to the weapon's low damage but high stagger it is best paired with other readily available damage sources like &lt;a href=\"Sentries\"&gt;Sentries&lt;/a&gt; and squad mates. Staggering the onslaught of enemies and giving your squad mates room to maneuver and finish them off, this is especially useful against &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;. "}
{"id": "4334", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4334", "title": "SOS Beacon", "text": "The SOS Beacon is a &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; that deploys a beacon that calls other Helldivers in orbit to your aid. \nThis will create a ping on the planet map making your icon more noticeable for potential reinforcements. Deploying SOS Beacon places your lobby in a high priority position, however, it does not guarantee that others will join your team. Deployed SOS Beacon will allow player to join you even if your lobby is private. \nIt is limited to one use and can kill enemies or destroy buildings when it is deployed"}
