{"id": "4633", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4633", "title": "Service Technician", "text": "The Service Technician is voiced by &lt;a href=\"https%3A//www.imdb.com/name/nm3076763/\"&gt;Sarah Elmaleh&lt;/a&gt;, the woman who stands next to the Engineering Bay with a gray hat on.\nThe Service Technician, as per her own voicelines, is in charge of maintaining all the machinery, gear, weapons and equipment aboard the Super Destroyer with the exception of the Eagle Fighter and the Pelican Transport Aircraft, both of which are served by a separate crew that can be seen on the (currently inaccessible) lower deck.\nJudging by their voicelines, the Service Technician comes from civil society, most likely having enlisted into the SEAF by the 16 years of age. While she admits to not having any children, her marital status is never made clear.\nMost of the voicelines that the Service Technician gives, whenever there aren't game-altering events such as the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Supercolony Crisis&lt;/a&gt; going on, serve to give players insight into what civil society looks like in the Federation, as many voicelines are about the Service Technician reminiscing about their childhood, festivities or other customs back at home and their individual hopes and dreams in regards to their military service.\nAlongside the &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Master\"&gt;Ship Master&lt;/a&gt;, the Service Technician is one of the 2 NPCs on the Super Destroyer that doesn't hail from Super Earth, but rather from an unknown planet colony."}
