{"id": "3797", "revid": "52438178", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3797", "title": "Shrieker", "text": "Shriekers are moderate-sized flying &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; with a large wingspan. They typically travel in large numbers and use dive tactics to swipe at Helldivers.\nThese flying menaces appeared shortly after the activation of the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;Terminid Control System&lt;/a&gt; on the Barrier Planets within the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Unconfirmed reports, antidemocratic rumors and unpatriotic conspiracy theories say that the Termicide, an Anti-Terminid Neurotoxin dispersed by the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;TCS Towers&lt;/a&gt;, is causing the Terminids to mutate and evolve faster.\nThe first official acknowledgement of Shriekers happened via an in-game intelligence brief on March 21st, 2024.\nBehavior.\nFrom observations and field studies by Helldivers, Shriekers greatly resemble &lt;a href=\"Hunter\"&gt;Hunters&lt;/a&gt; with abnormally large wings, with some suggesting that either the Termicide is affecting the stage between &lt;a href=\"Pouncer\"&gt;Pouncer&lt;/a&gt;s and Hunters, or the eggs themselves before they hatch. The fact Shriekers have their own nests makes the latter theory more likely.\nShriekers often attack in large packs, diving from a high angle attempting to slice open Helldivers and Citizens. If a Shrieker is killed while in the process of doing a dive attack, the corpse can still cause harm due to the sheer impact of the body.\nShriekers will almost always miss their attacks against Helldivers who are low to the ground, such as when prone/diving. Running is also a viable method to avoid attacks, as long as Shriekers don't fly in from directly in front or behind.\nShrieker Nest.\nShriekers spawn from tall towers known as a &lt;a href=\"Shrieker%20Nest\"&gt;Shrieker Nest&lt;/a&gt;. Capable of withstanding normal ammunition, it is advised to bring explosive launchers or stratagems to blow up these nests. Helldivers can call in a &lt;a href=\"NUX-223%20Hellbomb\"&gt;Hellbomb&lt;/a&gt; when close to the nest area. can also inflict major damage against a tower."}
{"id": "4341", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4341", "title": "Shrieker Nest", "text": "Shrieker Nests are a secondary mission objective found in every Challenging+ Helldiver operation within the Terminid front. The size of the nest's will always be the same regardless of the difficulty. These nests will continue to spawn large amounts of Shriekers until destroyed.\nShrieker Nests are a particularly dangerous sight as they spawn waves of &lt;a href=\"Shrieker\"&gt;Shrieker&lt;/a&gt;s; winged Terminid warriors that swoop down from the skies to perform hit-and-run attacks against Helldivers on the ground.\nIdentifying.\nAppearance wise, Shrieker nests look like three smaller spore spewers in a triangular formation and from a distance and up close will emit a bioluminescent yellow glow. Making target acquisition easy even in combat zones with high fog or spore density. However on planets that are more rocky or full of visual blockers, it may be hard to identify the nests.\nShrieker nests come in two types. Risen and Divet. Risen nests are elevated onto a oily rocky platform that all Terminid structures use, Divets are similar to regular nests and will be sunk into the ground with small Terminid walls around its perimeter. \nRisen are easier to deal with, mainly due to if a Helldiver is without long range equipment, then the elevation would buy time for a hellbomb to be activated. Divets however, are harder due to enemy accessing the Hellbomb easier. "}
