{"id": "5822", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5822", "title": "Spore Charger", "text": "The Spore Charger is a large, heavily armored &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt;. An evolution of the &lt;a href=\"Charger\"&gt;Charger&lt;/a&gt;, the Spore Charger is covered spores, causing it to be shrouded in fog."}
{"id": "4344", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4344", "title": "Spore Spewer", "text": "Spore Spewers are a &lt;a href=\"Objectives%23Tactical%20Objectives\"&gt;Secondary Objective&lt;/a&gt; and tactical asset in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;, which have a chance to appear in Medium or higher &lt;a href=\"Difficulty\"&gt;Difficulty&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;Missions&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Terminid Planets&lt;/a&gt;. Resembling large mushrooms, they present an environmental hazard to the Helldivers by constantly releasing thick clouds of spores into the air, greatly obscuring vision in a large area around it.\nIdentifying.\nThe presence of Spore Spewers on the map is relatively easy to spot depending on the planet terrain. On planets with little to no high terrain or hills, they can be seen from almost any distance on the map due to them emitting a very notable glow that can be seen through the dense clouds. Regardless of terrain, a thick green fog lingering around the Helldivers is a surefire way to identify that a Spore Spewer is nearby.\nStrategy.\nOn their own, Spore Spewers pose no more than a minor inconvenience to Helldivers, as their spores only obscure vision without dealing any kind of damage (akin to the &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Gas%20Strike\"&gt;Orbital Gas Strike&lt;/a&gt; Stratagem). Their threat level rises, however, when they are paired with large bug Patrols or positioned near critical objectives or bug Breaches. The reduced vision can, in those situations, often prove fatal to Helldivers, as it makes it far more difficult to spot priority enemies such as &lt;a href=\"Charger\"&gt;Chargers&lt;/a&gt; and camouflaged &lt;a href=\"Stalker\"&gt;Stalkers&lt;/a&gt; before they have already closed distance. If a firefight breaks out near Spore Spewers, destroying them should be a priority.\nSpewers themselves are easy to single out, provided one's minimap isn't obscured by atmospheric spores. They will always be found in very small bases with an oblong or circular profile on the minimap. If this is not available, they have a bright, bio-luminescent orange glow that can be seen from a distance.\nChanges to their has caused them to mutate and become far more dense compared to their original incarnation. It is no longer feasible to take them out with just thrown grenades. It now requires anti-structure weaponry or stratagems to take them down, such as the &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Precision%20Strike\"&gt;Orbital Precision Strike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eagle%20Airstrike\"&gt;Eagle Airstrike&lt;/a&gt;, or &lt;a href=\"FAF-14%20Spear\"&gt;FAF-14 Spear&lt;/a&gt;. If using stratagems against them, be sure to place them under the spewer's umbrella for best results, as a glancing explosion may fail to destroy them in one attack.\nIt should be noted that sometimes useful items such as &lt;a href=\"Ammunition\"&gt;Ammunition&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Samples\"&gt;Samples&lt;/a&gt; may spawn close or under the Spewer, therefore making it worth your while to check the destroyed stalk before moving on. Be cautious, as Terminids will be guarding the adjacent area."}
{"id": "3752", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3752", "title": "Spread Democracy", "text": "&lt;br&gt;\nSpread Democracy (also known as \"Raise the Flag\") is a mission in which Helldivers are tasked with planting and raising flags dotted around the map. Once within range of the objective and activated with its Stratagem Input (), a pod will crash onto the site and start to slowly raise a flag. At least one Helldiver is required to stay within the range of the flag or it will stop raising. After 1 minute and 40 seconds the flag will be successfully raised and the objective will be complete."}
