{"id": "6860", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6860", "title": "StA-X3 W.A.S.P. Launcher", "text": "The &lt;a href=\"https%3A//killzone.fandom.com/wiki/StA-X3_W.A.S.P._Launcher\"&gt;StA-X3 W.A.S.P. Launcher&lt;/a&gt; is an automatic multi-shot rocket launcher featured in &lt;a href=\"https%3A//killzone.fandom.com/wiki/Killzone_3\"&gt;Killzone 3&lt;/a&gt;. It is one of the first items available via collaboration between &lt;a href=\"Arrowhead%20Game%20Studios\"&gt;Arrowhead Game Studios&lt;/a&gt; and a guest developer\u2014in this case &lt;a href=\"https%3A//killzone.fandom.com/wiki/Guerrilla_Games\"&gt;Guerrilla Games&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe StA-X3 W.A.S.P. was gifted to all Helldivers on December 24, 2184, during the &lt;a href=\"Festival%20of%20Reckoning\"&gt;Festival of Reckoning&lt;/a&gt;.\nDesign.\nThe StA-X3 W.A.S.P. is a shoulder weapon (stock placed against shoulder) in the same vein as the &lt;a href=\"GL-21%20Grenade%20Launcher\"&gt;GL-21 Grenade Launcher&lt;/a&gt; (as opposed to other launchers that are shoulder-fired). It fires seven miniature rockets with fast speed and target-homing capability, going so far as to use the same aiming reticle as the &lt;a href=\"FAF-14%20Spear\"&gt;FAF-14 Spear&lt;/a&gt;. The rockets inflict explosive damage against targets. Its accompanying backpack provides spare five magazines.\nThe W.A.S.P. features two firing modes, a \"Burst\" mode firing rockets individually, and \"Artillery\" mode that launches all seven rockets at the same target. Upon exiting the barrel, each rocket curves upward and away, before accelerating to over 60m/s and seeking their designated target. The path each rocket takes is somewhat random, approaching from different angles.\nStratagem Code.\nPlayers must enter the following sequence, using the default Ctrl+WASD keys or the controller D-Pad in order to call down this single-use &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagem&lt;/a&gt; during a mission:"}
{"id": "5733", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5733", "title": "Stalker", "text": "The Stalker is a medium-sized &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; that comes from a Stalker Lair. They appear to be mutated &lt;a href=\"Hunter\"&gt;Hunters&lt;/a&gt; with camouflage capabilities and enhanced strength. There are reports that this appeared during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;.\nTheories claim that this camouflage ability was the result of Super Earth tampering with Terminid DNA to make them produce more E-710 or &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; had some kind of secret Terminid weaponization program in an attempt to create an army of controllable Terminid Stalkers to stealthily get rid of or assassinate separatists or rebel cells on planets within the Galactic Frontier. Ministry of Truth addendum: While gene splicing is common to produce higher-yielding E-710 specimens, the Ministry of Science would never create a strain of Terminid to police its own citizens. Such talk is dissident speak and the implication that rebels exist is tantamount to treason.\nBehavior.\nStalkers behave much like Hunters but with far greater health and the added threat of camouflage. Stalkers engage in hit-and-run tactics, often ambushing Helldivers from outside of their field of view, then retreating once taking enough damage, or their target is killed.\nThe Stalker's tongue attacks can knock down and ragdoll the player from a greater distance than its other attacks. This is particularly dangerous in certain areas, as while the tongue lash itself does relatively low damage, the real danger comes from its knockback that can fling Helldivers off lethal drops, into environmental hazards such as mines, into groups of other Terminids, or against solid surfaces.\nStalkers are lightly armored, but have high health pools and a head that is hard to hit. Coupled with their camouflage and fast movement speed, stalkers will likely reach and harm their target before fleeing or being put down, though with adequate warning and/or concentrated fire a team can dispatch a group of stalkers before they do any serious damage.\nWhen disengaging, Stalkers will leap high into the air and re-cloak themselves mid-flight. They will then retreat in a random direction for a time, only to attempt an ambush once more when their target has lost track of them. While cloaked, the Stalker can regenerate lost health, making them a persistent and frustrating threat.\nThe time a Stalker will spend retreating is randomized, as they sometimes attack again mere seconds later, and other times after minutes have passed. They however, will seem to step up their attacks if a Helldiver is operating an objective near them.\nStalker Lair.\nStalkers will only appear if the current mission contains a Stalker Lair. Lairs can be quite hard to find as unlike normal nests they are hidden on the map until discovered by a player or by activating a Radar Station. It's possible for multiple Stalker Lairs to spawn during a mission and once they're all destroyed, Stalkers will cease to spawn.\nEncountering Stalkers usually means their den is near, though some can travel considerable distances, particularly on higher difficulties. A Lair can be tracked by paying attention to where the Stalkers are coming from, as they will always come straight to the player from their nest, even if the Helldiver is prone and wearing scout armor."}
{"id": "6175", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6175", "title": "Stalker Lair", "text": "Stalker Lair are a secondary mission objective found in every difficulty 4 and above operation within the Terminid front. The size of the nest's will change depending on the difficulty along with the number of enemies capable of being deployed from the nest's emergence holes.\nStalker Nests are a particularly dangerous sight as they spawn waves of &lt;a href=\"Stalker\"&gt;Stalkers&lt;/a&gt;; mutated &lt;a href=\"Hunter\"&gt;Hunters&lt;/a&gt; that appear from thin air to perform hit-and-run attacks against Helldivers on the ground.\nIdentifying.\nThey look similar to a Terminid Nests, but can be identified specifically by the Large rock-like structures around the nest. If visual identification is difficult to confirm, it is best to utilize Radar Tower's or track the Stalker's themselves.\nLarger stalker nests are easier to identify due to the oily rock like structures built around the nests, these nests will be surrounded by a crescent shaped wall. Nest's are also able to be identified due to the orange pheromones being exhausted from the emergence holes. \nIf on combat zones that have intense spore coverage, utilization of SEAF tactical radar assets is recommended for proper identification of nests. If no such assets are available then utilizing a runner to ping nests is the best alternative.\nStructure Type's.\nThere are currently three types of Stalker Nest's, Light, Medium, and Heavy. \nLight Nests consist of only one hole and the nest will often be shaped like a crown or a moon on your map.\nMedium Stalker nests have one actual stalker one and one scavenger hole which will spawn 6 of them leading to a total of 8 Terminid units protecting the stalker nest. It is lighter in color than the light and it can look like a rocky rectangle on your map.\nThe heavy nest is the most dangerous as it consists of two stalker nests and can spawn 2-4 stalkers which can quickly overwhelm any helldiver team. It looks like a rocky oil rectangle, or a more elongated completed stalker map. \nStrategy.\nThe safest method to destroy them is by using an &lt;a href=\"Eagle%20Airstrike\"&gt;Eagle Airstrike&lt;/a&gt; as it will also clear out any Stalker's or chaff spawning, Alternative methods include the &lt;a href=\"EAT-17%20Expendable%20Anti-Tank\"&gt;EAT-17 Expendable Anti-Tank&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"GR-8%20Recoilless%20Rifle\"&gt;GR-8 Recoilless Rifle&lt;/a&gt;, and the &lt;a href=\"LAS-99%20Quasar%20Cannon\"&gt;LAS-99 Quasar Cannon&lt;/a&gt; are effective weapons to use against them as one shot from each will destroy a single nest. &lt;a href=\"Grenades%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;Grenades&lt;/a&gt; are also a viable choice, preferably standard grenade types. Special Grenade types will not work.\nStratagems such as the &lt;a href=\"Eagle%20Airstrike\"&gt;Eagle Airstrike&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Laser\"&gt;Orbital Laser Strike&lt;/a&gt;, or Orbital Barrages can also make short work of them in close proximity. A runner can be assigned to deliver the stratagem while the remaining teammates provide cover.\nClearing a nest is a risky method, as Stalkers can spawn en masse with chaff and overwhelm any potential Helldivers in the vicinity if not quick enough."}
{"id": "3861", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3861", "title": "Steeled Veterans", "text": "Steeled Veterans is a &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbond&lt;/a&gt; which released with the launch of &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Its primary focus relates to explosive/incendiary-type tools of destruction. It has 3 pages, containing various cosmetics, &lt;a href=\"Armory%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;armor&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"weapons\"&gt;weapons&lt;/a&gt;, and batches of Super Credits exchangeable for &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Medals\"&gt;Warbond Medals&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "3292", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3292", "title": "Sten Sector", "text": "The Sten Sector is a sector found on the &lt;a href=\"Eastern%20Front\"&gt;Eastern Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of 5 planets. Sten is a Scandinavian male given name. Literally meaning \"stone\", it derives from a literal translation of Peter into the North Germanic languages. Notable individuals with the name include. Sten Abel (1872\u20131942), Norwegian sailor.\nThe sector has been overrun by the Terminids ever since the start of galactic hostilities. As such the entire sector was quarantined by Super Earth High Command, and any attempts to retake them have been prohibited until very recently.\nAs the time went on, the Second Galactic War was declared, and eventually The Gloom began emerging in the Galaxy. Despite not originating from the sector, the interstellar spore cloud expanded till it consumed one of the sector's planets, &lt;a href=\"Azur%20Secundus\"&gt;Azur Secundus&lt;/a&gt;. Shortly after, Supply Lines were established, allowing for Helldivers to begin liberating the sector -- starting with the planet of &lt;a href=\"Trandor\"&gt;Trandor&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5833", "revid": "53862", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5833", "title": "Stim", "text": "Stims are part of a Helldiver's kit, used to heal damage taken while spreading Democracy.\nHelldivers 2.\nUsing a stim provides about four seconds of health and stamina regeneration, more than enough to return a Helldiver to full health. Stims will also instantly heal any limb or chest injuries. Regeneration continues even if the Helldiver continues to take moderate damage. If applied soon enough, stims can offset health lost while on &lt;a href=\"fire\"&gt;fire&lt;/a&gt; or immersed in &lt;a href=\"acid\"&gt;acid&lt;/a&gt;. Helldivers can support their injured teammates by pressing the [Interact] button when nearby. \nStims can be replenished from stim boxes found in field, through &lt;a href=\"Resupply\"&gt;Resupply&lt;/a&gt; Pods, or received from a &lt;a href=\"Backpacks%23Supply%20Pack\"&gt;Resupply Pack&lt;/a&gt;. Each pack provides a pair of stim injectors. Pressing the [Quick Stim] button while depleted will cause the Helldiver to exclaim they are out of stims.\nHelldivers typically drop in with two of four available stims, but can increase their load using the Hellpod Space Optimization &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Booster&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Armory%20%28Helldivers%202%29\"&gt;Armor sets&lt;/a&gt; with the Med-Kit ability increase the Helldiver's capacity to six stims, and increase the duration of their stims by 2 seconds.\nThe Experimental Infusion &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Booster&lt;/a&gt; causes stims to increase sprint speed by 10%, and reduces damage taken, but also affects the user's vision by giving them tunnel vision and altering perceived colors."}
