{"id": "3987", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3987", "title": "Super Destroyer", "text": "The Class 6 Series Crewed Interplanetary Combat Vessel, better known as the Super Destroyer, is a faster-than-light capable warship mass produced for use by the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; of the Super Earth Armed Forces (SEAF). Upon reading the &lt;a href=\"Helldiver%20Contract%20of%20Employment\"&gt;Contract of Employment&lt;/a&gt; and completing Helldiver training, each Helldiver is assigned command of a Super Destroyer to carry out their missions.\nGeneral.\nThe Super Destroyer is a relatively small combat vessel approximately 170 meters long and 80 meters wide. The Alcubierre Drive enables the Super Destroyer to navigate to any planet in the galaxy within seconds by warping time and space around the vessel. Super Destroyers are fueled by Element 710, an oil-like substance produced as a side-effect of &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; decomposition. Super Destroyers typically have names in the following format: SES (Super Earth Ship) \"Noun\" of \"Noun\", for example: SES \"Shield\" of \"the People\"; however the generic Super Destroyers seen in the distance are always labeled \"SS LIBERTY\". Players also have the choice to name their super destroyers at the start and any time during the game.\nExterior.\nThe rear consists of 10 large engines which the Super Destroyer uses to navigate local space around planets. The rear is flanked by two very large bracket-shaped panels that house the four outer engines. The middle hull consists of a large wide structure with what appear to be loading bays along the side. The front extends far over the bridge and consists of 2 long pillars flanking a larger center pillar, an antenna array stands at the tip of the center pillar.\nInterior.\nThe rear of the ship consists of the hangar where the &lt;a href=\"Pelican-1\"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt; is parked; on an upgraded Super Destroyer, the &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle&lt;/a&gt; is also parked in the hangar, and a large amount of ordinance is stored in the open. At the back of the hangar is a small access portal to the engine room. The main deck is an open area where the Ship Master and the Service Technician can be found. To the left is the Robotics Workshop and the Patriotic Administration Center, and on the right is the Cryogenic Chamber and the Engineering Workshop. The main deck also houses the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Citizen%20Edition\"&gt;Stratagem Hero arcade machine&lt;/a&gt; and a large television screen that shows news updates, commercials, and the 'Brasch Tactics' series of tips.\nThrough the first bulkhead is the Armory on the left and a series of computers on the right, the loading bays seen on the exterior of the ship are inaccessible and cannot be seen. Beyond the second bulkhead lies the Bridge where the Democracy Officer monitors the ship and its crew. A holographic is used by the Helldiver to select which planet to go to and which operation to take part in. At the foredeck is the launch system, for delivering Helldivers and their &lt;a href=\"Stratagems\"&gt;Stratagems&lt;/a&gt; to the field. It consists of four launch tubes, into which Helldivers and their resupplies are loaded. The observation deck allows the crew to directly monitor events on the ground, as well as inspect the ship's gun batteries and immediate surroundings.\nA belt of Hellpods encircles the deck of the Super Destroyer. An access port to starboard, next to the Robotics Workshop, allows a freshly-thawed Helldiver to enter the main deck. Helldivers from allied vessels can also return here to be re-frozen and transferred back to the ships they command. Additionally, two belts of artillery ammunition run along the ceiling of the bridge.\nArmament.\nSuper Destroyers are armed with a very wide variety of weapons mounted in front of and beneath the bridge. Visible weapons forward of the bridge include a one or two large cannons, two large self-loading rocket pods, and two large Gatling guns; 2 large triple-barreled naval guns are also visible mounted on the hull beneath the bridge. The only named weapon is the ATLAS Cannon, which fires the Precision Strike.\nThe Super Destroyer is capable of firing its precision ATLAS Cannon\u2014including specialized Gas, EMS, and Airburst shells\u2014a Gatling gun, 120mm and 380mm Artillery, a high intensity Laser, and a high velocity Railcannon.\nAmong the Super Destroyer's limited armament are the Helldivers themselves, of which four are devoted to each mission. This number can be adjusted using certain &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Boosters&lt;/a&gt;, or if the last remaining Helldiver demonstrates exceptional survival skills to merit defrosting an additional standby. Each allied Super Destroyer provides its own complement of Helldivers to the mission.\nGalactic travel.\nThe primary purpose of the Super Destroyer is to bring Helldivers to contested planets and support their operations on the ground. From the Galactic Map, Helldivers can select &lt;a href=\"Objectives\"&gt;Missions&lt;/a&gt; to undertake. Orbital thrusters are used to travel between mission sites on the same planet. By selecting a mission on another planet, the Helldiver can command the ship to warp to that planet.\nThe Super Destroyer generally cannot be commanded to travel to a fully liberated or a fully occupied planet. One general exception is made for travel to Mars, to replenish their supply of fully-trained recruits following their tutorial mission. A notable exception occurred during the last major operation on &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt;, when an immediate general retreat was issued as the planet collapsed under the influence of &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt;. The fleet retreated to Super Earth to regroup. Ships may still travel to Meridia, which has since become a black hole.\nInfrequently, a Super Destroyer may still be in orbit around a planet that has just been liberated or lost. If the Helldiver is in the middle of an operation, they may complete the rest of the operation before they must adhere to the retreat order. However, the operation may be more difficult as fewer Helldivers will be able to join.\nAllied travel.\nHelldivers can join their fellows by selecting their active mission sites, or using the Social menu interface. Allied Helldivers will remain aboard the squad leader's Super Destroyer in between missions, and drop in with the squad during missions. Players can leave the squad using the game menu, or by returning to the stasis pod chamber.\nOrbital support.\nDuring a mission, the Super Destroyer maintains an altitude of roughly one kilometer above the center of the mission area. This affects the angle at which orbital strikes impact the mission area\u2014nearly vertical towards the center of the map, and at more oblique angles towards the edge of a map. In some cases, very tall terrain or structures may prevent a strike from hitting its intended target.\nCircumstances may affect a Super Destroyer's ability to provide timely and accurate strikes, resulting in such missions being classed at a higher difficulty level. For instance, Atmospheric Interference makes it harder for the gun crews to stay on target, while Orbital Fluctuations force the Super Destroyer to devote more attention to maintaining position.\nThe Super Destroyer will maintain altitude until the mission timer expires, at which point it must return to low geostationary orbit. Stratagems then become unavailable (Excluding the &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20Artillery\"&gt;SEAF Artillery&lt;/a&gt; if the team has completed this sub-objective). Reinforcements will also be unavailable, forcing the Helldivers on the ground to rely on their dropped assets. Finally, an emergency shuttle will be launched, which starts the extraction timer.\nShould a Helldiver threaten to abandon their mission by being outside the mission boundary too long, immediate judgment is passed upon the offender. The newly-branded traitor will thereafter be targeted by the Super Destroyer's artillery, unless they somehow manage to reach the extraction shuttle.\nShip module upgrades.\nPatriotic Administration Center.\nDonation Access License: \"Purchases permanent access to ammo provided by the \"Support Our Heros\" fund, which allows patriotic family members to donate supplies to their loved ones in the field.\"\nStreamlined Request Process: \"Pre-approves the following forms in the Support Weapon Approval Process: Form 99-C (Justification for Munitions), Form 88-1 (Democratic Impact Worksheet), &amp; Form 104 (Collateral Damage Risk Waiver).\"\nHand Carts: \"Provides hand carts which can carry multiple backpack stratagems from storage, decreasing both reload time and crew lumbar injuries.\"\nSuperior Packing Methodology: \"Authorizes an 8-week crew training course in Superior Packing Methodology (SPM), resulting in increased supply box capacity.\"\nPayroll Management System: \"Top-of-the-line accounting software automates payroll calculations, freeing up HR associates to lubricate support weapons in their spare time.\"\nOrbital Cannons.\nExploding Shrapnel: \"Military watchdog groups have called exploding shrapnel \"savage,\" \"merciless,\" and \"well-suited for spreading Democracy.\"\nMore Guns: \"After years of research into improving the Super Destroyer's firepower, the Ministry of Science concluded that the most effective method was adding more guns.\"\nZero G Breech Loading: \"Replaces the current method of loading cannons - manual shell insertion down the front of the barrel - with rear loading, which is much faster.\"\nAtmospheric Monitoring: \"Grants subscription to data stream of live weather conditions, allowing for increased accuracy in orbital targeting.\"\nHigh-Density Explosives: \"Removes stabilising phlematiser agents from explosive material used to pack orbital shells, allowing for more powerful payloads.\"\nHangar.\nLiquid-Ventilated Cockpit: \"Fills cockpit with breathable liquid perfluorocarbons, which absorb g-forces and thereby enable pilots to conduct tighter turns without losing consciousness.\"\nPit Crew Hazard Pay: \"Authorizes hazard pay for pit crews, allowing them to reload the Eagle Fighter in-spaceflight.\"\nExpanded Weapons Bay: \"Trims excess leg space in the cockpit, allowing the Eagle to carry additional payloads.\"\nXXL Weapons Bay: \"Further expands Eagle weapons bay by removing unnecessary systems such as fire suppression, ejection, and airbags.\"\nAdvanced Crew Training: \"Trains pit crew members to employ situational protocol adaptations, such as leaving unused ammo loaded instead of replacing it.\"\nBridge.\nTargeting Software Upgrade: \"Increases orbital targeting speed by updating cannon targeting software to premium version.\"\nNuclear Radar: \"Increases the range of Helldiver Radar by equipping it with a high-powered Plutonium-210 battery.\"\nPower Steering: \"Installs electronic actuators that augment the standard method of manual, foot-operated Hellpod steering.\"\nEnhanced Combustion: \"Increases burning temperature of incendiary weapons by lacing fuel with a precisely-formulated compound of &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thermite\"&gt;thermite&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/White_phosphorus_munitions\"&gt;white phosphourus&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capsaicin\"&gt;capsaicin&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"https%3A//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allyl_isothiocyanate\"&gt;allyl isothiocyanate&lt;/a&gt;, and 19 other accelerants.\"\nMoral Augmentation: \"Boost overall crew efficiency with a suite of proven enthusiasm enhancement initiatives, such as citizenship anniversary celebrations and paid lavatory breaks.\"\nEngineering Bay.\nSynthetic Supplementation: \"Integrates moderate doses of amphetamines and androgenic steriods into diet of loading crew, leading to increased pace, focus, &amp; stamina, among other effects.\"\nAdvanced Construction: \"Reinforces sentries with state-of-the-art cyanoacrylate adhesives, greatly improving their durability under fire.\"\nRapid Launch System: \"Jump-starts Hellpod firing with an immediate TNT detonation at the time of launch.\"\nCircut Expansion: \"Augments electrical weaponry by safely connecting multiple interior arc extenders into one linear chain.\"\nStreamlined Launch Process: \"Decreases time to initiate deployment of Support Weapon Stratagems by removing dialogue box confirming intent to fire.\"\nRobotics Workshop.\nDynamic Tracking: \"Repurposed surveillance technology allows the Sentry Deployment Cannon to closely track the user at all times, no matter where they go or what they do, ready to fire at any second.\"\nShock Absorption Gel: \"Lines Sentry pods with shock-absorbing hydrogel, allowing extra ammunition to be packed in the space previously occupied by shock-absorbing springs.\"\nHigh-Quality Lubricant: \"Applies the cear-frictionless lubricant known as \"Super Jelly\" to sentry ring mounts, facilitating extremely smooth mechanical operation.\"\nBlast Absorption: \"Reinforces sentries with expanded polystyrene pieces (peanut-shaped variety), which absorb thermal and blast energy.\"\nCross-Platform Compatibility: \"Allows Mortar Targeting Platform to access Helldiver HUD ecosystem through use of third-party conversion software.\""}
{"id": "2760", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=2760", "title": "Super Earth", "text": "Super Earth is one of two inhabited planets that are in the &lt;a href=\"Sol%20System\"&gt;Sol System&lt;/a&gt;. It is the home world of Humanity and the capital planet of the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. \nGeography.\nSuper Earth, being the shining bastion of Prosperity, Liberty and Managed Democracy that it has always been, is possibly the only planet in the entire galaxy to feature multiple biomes. However, due to the Great War, its northern hemisphere has been rendered partially uninhabitable. Nevertheless, Super Earth managed to eventually optimize itself into seven separate sectors.\nSector 1.\nFormerly known as \"Oceania\", this sector is mostly comprised of an arid desert continent formally known as Australia, along with several tropical islands, archipelagos, and peninsulas that once formed part of a continent called \"Asia\". It is the home of Mega City 1.\nSector 2.\nMuch of Sector 2 consists of lands formerly known as \"China\" and \"Asia\", with territory stretching north into the area once known as \"Mongolia\" and \"Siberia\". The eastern and central parts of this sector are mostly comprised of ancient mountains and forests. Deserts and parts of an arid steppe are found to the north and west. Wild horsemen once roamed freely in this land, the spirit of Freedom burning ablaze in their hearts. This Sector is home to the Great Wall of Democracy, as well as Mega City 2.\nSector 3.\nFormerly known as \"Russia\" by some, and \"Scandinavia\" by others, this sector is mostly comprised of cold mountains, tundras, fjords and ice fields that will freeze the enemies of freedom. To its north and south lie wasteland zones that cannot be inhabited, being products of the Great War. This Sector is home to Prosperity City, the illustrious capital of the Federation of Super Earth. This sector also consists of two islands formerly known as \"Greenland\" and \"Iceland\", as well as being home to the Emergency Seed Vault on an island formerly known as \"Svalbard.\"\nSector 4.\nFormerly known as \"Europe\", this Sector is one of the most urbanized in Super Earth, having seen the lion's share of Super Earth's foundational history. To its north lies a now-uninhabitable set of islands formerly known as \"The British Isles\". These isles are speculated to be where the phrase \"How about a nice cup of Liber-tea!\" originated from. This Sector is the home of Mega City 4, and the landscape consists of plains, mountains, and forests. Its southern portion shares the ancient continent of \"Africa\" with Sector 5, covering much of the western Sahara Desert and the Atlas Mountains.\nSector 5.\nFormerly known by the names of \"India\" and \"Arabia\", Sector 5 consists of many different lands. It encapsulates areas formerly known as the \"Arabian Peninsula\", \"India\", the southern portion of the ancient continent of \"Asia\", and the easternmost portion of the ancient continent of \"Africa\" in which it is rumoured that the first humans were born. Much of the sector is dry and hot, with over half of the sector consisting of scorching deserts. It possesses two of the last three remaining rainforests and is home to Mega City 5 and the Pyramids of Super Earth.\nSector 6.\nFormerly known as \"Latin America\", Sector 6 consists of the Central and Southern portions of the ancient continent of \"America\". It also manages the southern portions of the land formerly known as \"the United States of America\". This sector is home to Mega City 6 and houses one of the last three remaining rainforests.\nSector 7.\nFormerly known as \"the United States of America\", Sector 7 consists of the Northern portions of the ancient continent of \"America\". This Sector is rumoured to have been the birthplace of Super Earth's core tenets of Freedom and Democracy, with its inhabitants having a reputation of high patriotism and love for their compatriots, values that would later be imprinted into all Super Earth citizens.\nSector 7 is home to to Mega City 7, as well as Superstone Park.\nOceans and Poles.\nSuper Earth's mass is comprised of around 70% water, which required the division of its water masses into 3 sections:\nThere used to be permafrost ice caps on both the north and south poles of Super Earth known as \"Antarctica\" and \"the Arctic\". However, these ice caps were melted away at some point prior to the First Galactic War, as their ice was incapable of sustaining all of mankind's prosperity.\nHistory.\nCreation of Earth.\nSuper Earth, or Earth as it was previously known, was formed 4.5 billion years ago. It was a planet comparable to &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt; with extreme temperatures and oceans of lava. Later on, a planet roughly the same size as &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;, named Thea, collided with Earth. The rock and debris from this collision formed a ring around the Earth until it eventually coalesced into the Super Moon.\nLife on Earth.\nThe planet eventually began to cool, and oceans of liquid water would cover most of its surface. Life would come to thrive on the planet, and some creatures went on to colonize the land, one day evolving into Humans.\nAncient Civilisations.\nThe first Human civilization was located in Mesopotamia. Other civilizations arose in Greece, Egypt, India, China, and Central America. These societies were mostly agricultural, located near rivers and fertile land.\nModern Civilization.\nAn Industrial Revolution took over the world with the invention of steam power, allowing for the entire world to be colonized and claimed. Millions found employment, and the economy flourished. One hundred years after the first Industrial Revolution, the first major global conflict would begin, known as World War One. The war would grip the world for four long years until the Treaty of Versailles ended the war on November 11th, 1918. Twenty-one years of peace would come to pass until World War Two, lasting six years and ending with a Japanese surrender on September 2nd, 1945. The post-war world would find itself embroiled in a Cold War between the victors of World War Two, the United States and the Soviet Union. The Cold War lasted for 44 years and ended with the collapse of the Soviet Union on December 26th, 1991.\nThe Great War.\nThe exact year in which the Great War began is lost to time, but it likely happened sometime between 2015 to 2044. The war most likely included the United States, United Kingdom, Russia, and China. Most of Russia's population centres were wiped out along with the United Kingdom, as well as some parts of Alaska, Siberia, and Canada. Although the conflict utilized nuclear weapons, it left the United States and China mostly unscathed.\nUnification of Earth and Establishment of the Federation of Super Earth.\nOut of the dust of the Great War, one government stood tall. They created a new way of government, Managed Democracy, and achieved total unification of the planet to a previously unseen extent. They ventured far out into space, proclaiming themselves as the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, thusly creating a utopia of Freedom and Prosperity. No enemy of the Federation has ever even come close to contesting with Super Earth, not even a &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;three front war&lt;/a&gt; against Humanity could threaten them. However, recent events have been painting a worrying picture. &lt;a href=\"The%20Gloom\"&gt;The Gloom&lt;/a&gt; creeps across the Galaxy with no sign of stopping, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; have encroached on Federation space to get as close as one sector away from the home of Managed Democracy, and the &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;Illuminate&lt;/a&gt; have returned after a hundred year exile, abducting Super Earth citizens for vile purposes."}
{"id": "6382", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6382", "title": "Super Earth Armed Forces", "text": "The Super Earth Armed Forces (S.E.A.F.) are the armed forces of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;. The S.E.A.F. is split into different branches, including the Super Earth Army, Navy, Colonial Guard and of course the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt;, whom receive their &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;orders&lt;/a&gt; directly from High Command. Raw recruits typically go through a rigorous 72-hour S.E.A.F. basic training course, before being assigned to a branch or being given more specialized training, such as the 8-week Superior Packing Methodology (SPM) training course for Super Destroyer crews, or the \"Real Deal\" Helldiver training on &lt;a href=\"Mars\"&gt;Mars&lt;/a&gt;.\nSEAF Branches.\nNote: The following is based on both in game sources and also a heavy amount of speculation. The &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt; also have their own page. For more on the Ministry which the SEAF is subordinate to, see the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defense&lt;/a&gt;.\nSuper Earth Army.\nWhilst the Helldivers are the scalpel of the military might of &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, the regular army corps are its hammer, responsible for the bulk of the fighting in the Galactic War, as well as taking over more permanent security duties over liberated planets. While the exact strength of the Army Corps is highly classified, the army is likely the largest of the branches in sheer numbers as they can hold multiple fronts on dozens of planets -- something that will likely require vast reserves of manpower numbering in the tens of billions.\nBefore the official declaration of the Second Galactic War however, the bulk of the Army was on a peacetime standing, spread across the frontiers of the federation maintaining security over various military installations, forward command bases, outposts, communication arrays and training facilities. This paltry peacetime peacekeeper force has also since been reinforced with billions of \"voluntary conscripts\" following the official declaration of the Galactic War on Tyranny on May 15th, 2184, with new recruits rushed through basic training to reinforce frontlines and help establish critical infrastructure to train more conscripted volunteers.The Army possesses overwhelming firepower in the form of &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20Artillery\"&gt;heavy artillery&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Launch%20ICBM\"&gt;ICBM&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20SAM%20Site\"&gt;SAM sites&lt;/a&gt;, as well as armored vehicles such as &lt;a href=\"EXO-45%20Patriot%20Exosuit\"&gt;exosuits&lt;/a&gt; and (the latter of which the automatons have made inferior copies). Additionally, the Army is the branch from which the Helldivers are drafted from, at least during the First Galactic War.\nTheir bravery in the face of overwhelming odds and anti-democratic values cannot be understated. High Command maintains that any lost ground is a temporary tactical decision to draw the enemy into the blinding light of justice and liberty. The Army has never suffered a (total) defeat, but has willingly expended lives in the pursuit of drawing the enemies of Democracy into traps or fighting valiant delaying actions to allow for civilians to evacuate safely.\nEven when forced to withdraw from a planet, the Army will simply lick its wounds and return in greater force. Even so, individual casualties are high, and soldiers deployed to exceptionally hazardous postings will be granted an increase in citizenship class for themselves and their immediate families upon mission completion or death.\nEngineering corps.\nThe Super Earth Army also possesses its own Engineering corps, responsible for building various SEAF installations, such as the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;TCS Towers&lt;/a&gt; and the Orbital Defenses of the Menkent Line. The Engineering corps also provides technical support and repairs (as seen when the communication array on &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt; was knocked out). These military engineering units will sometimes be supplemented with civilian contractors when necessary.\nAnother notable branch of the Super Earth Army (likely operating under the S.E.A.F. engineering corps) is the Excavation Corps; who were founded by SGM Janet Jones, who famously said that \"The ground is just another obstacle that hasn't yet been cleared.\" The Excavation Corps are an engineering unit that are presumably responsible for systematic drilling and blasting for surface excavations deemed strategically valuable. They make heavy use of explosives and the &lt;a href=\"Democratic%20Detonation\"&gt;CE-27 Ground Breaker&lt;/a&gt; armor.\nPresumably they were on the ground of Planet X-45 uncovering the formerly lost Advanced Weapons Lab built there by Super Earth. Their founders motto of the ground being just another obstacle that hasn't yet been cleared has became iconic to all those who've worked alongside the Excavation Corps. A specialized set of gear was also developed for them, known as the CE-27 Ground Breaker armor, which allowed for the carrying of additional explosives.\n&lt;a href=\"Viper%20Commandos\"&gt;Viper Commandos&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Viper Commandos are a storied S.E.A.F. special operations unit whose real exploits are portrayed in the classic comic book series \"Tales of the Viper Commandos\". For example, Jackle 6, a veteran of the Viper Commandos in the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; (whose uniform became the basis for the &lt;a href=\"PH-9%20PREDATOR\"&gt;PH-9 PREDATOR&lt;/a&gt; Medium Armour) held off an entire &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminid&lt;/a&gt; brood on &lt;a href=\"Nublaria%20I\"&gt;Nublaria&lt;/a&gt;, a planet in the Celeste Sector, with nothing but a &lt;a href=\"MG-43%20Machine%20Gun\"&gt;machine gun&lt;/a&gt;, pocket knife, and &lt;a href=\"Orbital%20Laser\"&gt;Orbital Laser Strikes&lt;/a&gt;.\n&lt;a href=\"Freedom%27s%20Flame\"&gt;361st Freedom's Flame&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe 361st \"Freedom's Flame\" Unit was an S.E.A.F special operations unit whose final mission is documented in the graphic novel \"The Breach\", in which the entire unit was deployed right into the heart of a Supervolcano located in an unknown planet that was once besieged by a massive swarm of Terminids. The entire unit would be wiped out after they triggered an eruption in order to wipe out the Terminids.\n&lt;a href=\"Chemical%20Agents\"&gt;Chemical Agents and Division Zero&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Chemical Agents, also known as the Noxious Rangers, are the division of the Super Earth Armed Forces tasked with defending against and using chemical and biological weapons. Unfortunately due to a lax in proper distancing rules, an unfortunate outbreak of Carcino-Plague was caused, with many of Super Earth's citizens being consequently infected.\nBut from tragedy would be born hope, as the bio-warfare pioneers of Division Zero would be conscripted from the quarantine zones and hospices to spread their Carcino-Plague on the battlefield. The incident would be immortalized through &lt;a href=\"Patient%20Zero%27s%20Remembrance\"&gt;Patient Zero's Remembrance&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Standard%20of%20Safe%20Distance\"&gt;Standard of Safe Distance&lt;/a&gt;, so that their sacrifice might be remembered and that another unfortunate outbreak of Carcino-Plague would never happen again.\nSuper Earth Navy.\nBy far the largest and most sought after branch within the Super Earth Armed Forces, the Super Earth Navy is Super Earth's aerospace service branch, responsible for maintaining and crewing its space borne warships like the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Liberty-Class%20Cruiser\"&gt;Liberty-Class Cruiser&lt;/a&gt;, as well as aircraft such as the &lt;a href=\"Pelican-1\"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle&lt;/a&gt;, and a fleet of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth%20Bomber\"&gt;bombers&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe Navy's primary mission is to defend and spread freedom and economic prosperity by providing orbital support to S.E.A.F. forces planetside. They are also responsible for maintaining orbital dominance and keeping the Faster-Than-Light Lanes open, as well as transporting military personnel and equipment wherever they are needed. Many in the outer colonies seek to join the Navy as their way to do their part for Super Earth and see the stars, filling the ranks of &lt;a href=\"Service%20Technician\"&gt;technicians&lt;/a&gt;, navigators, &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Master\"&gt;officers&lt;/a&gt;, communication operators and weapon specialists.\nUnsurprisingly, the Super Earth Navy is the current dominant spaceborne navy in the Galaxy. The only other fleet that comes anywhere close to matching the Super Earth Navy is the Automaton fleet, with tens of thousands of &lt;a href=\"Automaton%20Fleet%20Destroyer\"&gt;Automaton Fleet Destroyers&lt;/a&gt;. The Navy's arsenal ranges from the modern Super Destroyer to the larger Liberty-Class Cruisers, to the many orbital space stations and defense platforms that protect many a world.\nThough the figures of its exact size are unclear, the Super Earth Navy is likely the Galaxy's most powerful navy, as well as the most numerous, with numbers clocking in at over twelve million active vessels (based on Helldiver numbers, as each active diver gets a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;). While the primary warship of the Super Earth Navy is the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;, the navy also possesses heavier warships in the form of the &lt;a href=\"Liberty-Class%20Cruiser\"&gt;Liberty-Class Cruiser&lt;/a&gt;, which presumably surpasses the Destroyer in both size and armament. The pride of the Navy however is the Democracy Space Station, a colossal battle station that is equal parts battleship, carrier and logistical support vessel, the &lt;a href=\"DSS\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt; is the most powerful strategic tool in the Navy's current arsenal.\nDemocracy Class Interplanetary Battle Stations.\nWhile the details of the project remain highly classified, during the First Galactic War, an advanced weapons lab on the planet &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; was working on the development of a powerful interplanetary battle station. However, the project was abandoned along with the laboratory (and the planet) due to high levels of radiation on X-45 -- possibly following the responsible use of planet-wide nuclear weapons bombardment.\nAfter months of intense research, on September 25th, 2184, (almost) final plans for the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; were approved and construction of was finally ready to begin (once the planet of &lt;a href=\"Gaellivare\"&gt;Gaellivare&lt;/a&gt; was liberated). The DSS promises to be a powerful strategic tool for reshaping the Galactic Map \u2014 democratically directed by the Helldivers themselves. Details on the exact layout and capabilities of the DSS are naturally highly classified. However, the construction site of the space station itself utterly dwarfs the &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyers&lt;/a&gt; of the Super Earth Navy.\nConstruction would officially complete on November 13th, 2184, with the Station completing it's trials and first test fire against a small moon later that day, before being immediately commissioned into the Super Earth Navy. However rather than be under regular navy control, the decision was made by High Command to have the station itself be controlled collectively by the Helldiver Corps, via the Galactic Map. Whilst it was hoped that the defenders of humanity would know the best way to defend our way of life and fight for Managed Democracy, sadly this system of command and control has proven to be... temperamental...\nNever the less, the station's advantages make up for the flaws of it's commanders (and billions of super credits to operate). The station protected by hardened (but lightweight) alloy plating and armed with a suite of 77 PRESIDENTIAL-Class Cannons and of course it's Zero G Anti-Ship Missile System. The station also acts as a massive super-carrier, housing a massive fleet of Eagle fighters in an equally massive three-tiered Convocation Bay. No other ship in the Super Earth Navy can compete, although for the time being only one such battle station exists in the Galaxy, thus it's weaponry of mass liberation must be used sparingly.\nAuxiliary and civilian transports.\nOf course not every vessel put to the stars by humanity belongs to the Super Earth Navy, nor is everyone lucky enough to crew a &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyer&lt;/a&gt;, pilot an &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle Fighter&lt;/a&gt;, or be assigned as one of the 1.3 million personnel aboard the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;. As the great philosopher of Warfare Sun Tzu once said: \"The line between disorder and order lies in logistics.\"\nFoodstuffs to feed the hungry, materials to make implements of war and patriotic volunteers willing to throw themselves into the line of fire need to be transported around the galaxy somehow. Thus whilst it might not be as exciting as laying waste to an entire planet from low orbit, logistical craft are as much of a vital component to any military campaign as Super Destroyers, though rarely if ever do they get as much attention and hardly any glory.\nThe Super Earth Navy of course maintains it's own fleet of Faster than Light Capable military transports and lander, although the transport of militarily non-strategic cargo, civilians and cargo through space is still facilitated in non military transports -- particularly during planetary evacuations and the settling of new worlds.\nSuch civilian vessels are large, unarmed, unarmored and unprepared, making them vulnerable to attack by malicious forces who would seek to destroy or capture their valuable cargo. This further reinforces the importance of the navy's vital mission of keeping the the space lanes clear of the enemies of freedom and open for all traffic, military, commercial or otherwise.\nColonial Defense Forces.\nThe brave individuals of the colonies are given extensive military and survival training to further augment S.E.A.F. force projection. Every person, man, woman, child, and pet are expected to give their life without question in protecting Super Earth's legal holdings. To this end, the colonies of Super Earth possess their own security forces and colonial militias, funded in part by the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt;. In theory, a well regulated planetary security force backed up by colonial militiamen would be able to wage a successful guerrilla war against enemy invaders thanks to their greater knowledge of the local terrain and the fact that the colonists would be fighting to defend their homes.\nHowever these security forces have proven insufficient in the current conflict, thus showing the barbarity and inhumanity of Super Earth's enemies. They are willing to kill voters who were equipped, within regulation, for the past one hundred years of peacetime for policing and protecting against wildlife. While well equipped with valor, the colonial security forces are nowhere near as well equipped or trained as the rest of S.E.A.F.\nDue to limited need in peacetime, budget cuts for many colonies have also pulled out what few teeth they still have, possibly contributing to swift fall of many planets near the start of the Second Galactic War. A prime example of this is the first defense of &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, where the spawning hordes of &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; easily overwhelmed the planet's colonial militias in a matter of hours. Even so, individual heroism has been noted among the colonial militia, with reports of Helldivers coming across dead citizens who managed to destroy &lt;a href=\"Devastator\"&gt;Devastators&lt;/a&gt; using &lt;a href=\"SG-88%20Break-Action%20Shotgun\"&gt;double barrel shotguns&lt;/a&gt; and, in some cases, shovels.\nAs per S.E.A.F. policy, such valiant heroes will posthumously have their citizenship level raised and thus garner the right to have their name listed in the planetary death log (subject to Ministry of Truth regulations).\nSEAF Bug Wardens.\nWhile the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt; are a threat that will infest the entire galaxy if not suppressed, they are also a rare and valuable species that is potentially an unlimited source of E-710 fuel for Super Earth. Outright extermination of the Terminids is counterproductive from both a logistical and moral perspective. Thus, after the defeat of the Bugs during the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, they were confined to farms to be bred, raised, and harvested in order to produce E-710. This farming would last all through the Great Democratisation until February 8th, 2184. Billions of Terminids rose up and overran the Eastern sectors, marking one of the two starting events of the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;. While attempts were later made to introduce Terminids to safer, more free range farms, the fruits of these efforts have generally been mixed.\nWith the establishment of a Terminid Research Preserve on Acamar IV, past lessons learned from the failure of the Terminid Farms have been applied to guarantee the Preserve's security. The Terminids will to be allowed to develop naturally, but their population is monitored at all times by S.E.A.F. Wardens and encircled by electrical fencing, above and below ground. In the unlikely event of a containment breach, nuclear bombardments are set to automatically trigger. Research teams stationed within the Preserve will be able to requisition Terminid specimens as needed, aided by S.E.A.F. Bug Wardens.\nThe role of these wardens is to help enforce the Terminid's preservation as well as to manage and protect the various specimens within the Preserve. In the future, it is hoped that the Preserve can be expanded to provide not only research specimens, but also easy-to-acquire E-710. While these endeavors may present risks, it is necessary for the construction of the DSS and the long-term security of Managed Democracy itself.\nExcitingly, a small part of the Preserve has been allocated to the new \"Tyranny Park,\" where adventurous and well-paying citizens will be able to observe the Terminids in their natural environment. Some particularly bold patriots may even participate in a Big Tyrant Hunt. This exciting venture will help fund future research and deepen our citizens' understanding of the horrors of Tyranny.\nSEAF High Command.\nUnsurprisingly, Super Earth High Command stands as the primary command structure of the Super Earth Armed Forces. Headquartered on Super Earth and staffed by the most well connected greatest strategic minds from across the Federation, High Command's purpose is to direct the Super Earth Armed Forces to assure they meet the demands of Super Earth across the galaxy -- whether it be defending the freedom of words or launching campaigns to retake lost ground, it all has to start somewhere.\nBeing high up in the Super Earth food chain -- as the rank and file say -- High Command works in conjunction with the various &lt;a href=\"Ministries%20and%20Megacorporations\"&gt;Ministries and Megacorporations&lt;/a&gt; within the Federation who provide the administrative and logistical backbone of the Super Earth Armed Forces in the form of logistical, industrial, political, technological and administrative support. Primarily though, High Command reports to the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Defense\"&gt;Ministry of Defence&lt;/a&gt;. The chain of command likely runs from the &lt;a href=\"President\"&gt;President&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; to the Ministry of Defense, then to the various commanders of the combatant commands which make up the SEHC, including both famous wartime such as &lt;a href=\"General%20Brasch\"&gt;General Brasch&lt;/a&gt; and lesser known pencil pushers unproven but eager commanders just waiting to prove themselves.\nHigh Command has the authority to carry out exactly what needs to be done to defend Managed Democracy against the enemies of Super Earth and her people. To this end, during these times of war, High Command distributes &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders\"&gt;Major Orders&lt;/a&gt; to all forces within the S.E.A.F, setting major objectives that must be achieved. The Helldivers particularly are given the most critical orders and are demanded to accomplish these tasks, no matter the odds. Because of this, High Command often provides the Helldivers with (nearly) any piece of equipment needed to get the job done, including both mass manufactured classics and experimental armaments.\nAdditionally following intelligence and command failures following the Automaton Reclamation and fall of the &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt; Line, High Command has started to more actively communicate with the Helldivers, providing the latest frontline intelligence from the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Intelligence\"&gt;Ministry of Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; through the galactic map and dispatches. After all, knowing is half the battle, the other being freedom and heavy ordinance...\nPossible SEAF Doctrine (speculation).\nDespite possessing deep manpower reserves and awesome firepower, S.E.A.F. forces are often &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;outnumbered&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;outgunned&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=\"Illuminate\"&gt;outclassed&lt;/a&gt;, showing that continual sacrifice and military spending are required by Super Earth. This has resulted in Super Earth being slowly worn down and destroyed adopting a strategy of tactical advances to defensive lines away from the enemy in order to preserve its manpower and equipment.\nAlthough the exact doctrine of S.E.A.F. forces is unclear classified, one possible strategy employed is a \"Hammer and Scalpel\" doctrine that relies on cooperation between all branches, much like the Federation itself.\nThe Super Earth Army holds the frontlines, enduring the full might of enemy forces, whilst the Helldivers -- with orbital support from the Navy -- deploy deep behind enemy lines where they cripple key objectives, disrupt enemy logistics and cause general chaos. This gives the Army the chance to push forward and liberate some ground, increasing a planet's liberation progress. Once all enemy resistance has collapsed and all ground is taken, the planet will be officially liberated, with S.E.A.F. forces then transitioning to occupation, cleanup, and reconstruction operations in the aftermath.\nS.E.A.F. Soldiers.\nThe standard issue kit of most S.E.A.F. ground soldiers is not too dissimilar from those worn by the now defunct United Nations Peacekeepers, though unlike their distant ancestors, S.E.A.F. soldiers have real guns.\nOver the top of white-blue combat fatigues is worn a set of standard issue B-01 blue tactical armor, which provides basic protection from both pistol and rifle caliber bullets, as well as stab and slash attacks aimed at the chest. S.E.A.F. ground soldiers are also provided with a tactical belt with several pouches for storing ammunition and other items. Additional knee and thigh guards are worn for extra protection, as well as a fully enclosed combat helmet which can be worn alongside a set of protective goggles. Finally, the most important part of the standard issue kit is a pair of leather-nylon combat boots, which are an essential part of any S.E.A.F. soldier's uniform.\nThe Super Earth Armed Forces possess a vast arsenal of equipment, with the standard infantrymen being armed much like freshly defrosted Helldivers with standard issue &lt;a href=\"AR-23%20Liberator\"&gt;AR-23 Liberator&lt;/a&gt; Assault Rifle and a &lt;a href=\"P-2%20Peacemaker\"&gt;P-2 Peacemaker&lt;/a&gt; Sidearm as a backup weapon. Infantry squads will also sometimes contain specialists armed with heavier weapons such as sniper rifles, disposable rocket launchers and man portable rail-guns, although the &lt;a href=\"MG-43%20Machine%20Gun\"&gt;MG-43 Machine Gun&lt;/a&gt; seems to be the most common -- acting as the Squad Automatic Weapon.\nEven before the declaration of the Second Galactic War, S.E.A.F. soldiers were deployed in large numbers to protect remote S.E.A.F. facilities and colonies from enemy aggression. Unfortunately, while the S.E.A.F. overall is unbeatable (as mentioned previously), casualties for individual units are extremely high. Furthermore, the Helldivers primarily deploy behind enemy lines, and as such, the only S.E.A.F. soldiers that they are likely to find are those who have already given their lives for the defense of Super Earth.\nSEAF Training Facilities.\nFour &lt;a href=\"SEAF%20Training%20Facilities\"&gt;SEAF Training Facilities&lt;/a&gt; were built after the &lt;a href=\"Major%20Orders%23Declaration%20of%20the%20Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Declaration of the Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; and gave a 1.5% liberation boost. Although two of the facilities fell to the Automatons, the other two managed to survive until they were shut down on June 4th, taking the liberation boost with them."}
{"id": "5157", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5157", "title": "Super Earth Bomber", "text": "Aside from the common &lt;a href=\"Eagle\"&gt;Eagle&lt;/a&gt; fighters and &lt;a href=\"Pelican-1\"&gt;Pelican&lt;/a&gt; dropships, the Super Earth Armed Forces also make use of a long range bomber aircraft that is approximately double the size of the aforementioned aircraft. The primary role of the BT-1317 Bomber is to presumably drop bombs, launch torpedoes and deploy air-launched cruise missiles.\nWhilst the capabilities and official designation for this aircraft is unavailable due to none being assigned to the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver corps&lt;/a&gt; (yet). Some Helldivers have jokingly referred to it as the \"Albatross\" after noticing the similarities between it and the Pelican, usually after coming across the (rare) wreckage of the bomber crashed sparsely across enemy controlled planets. Internally this aircraft has also been referred to as the BT-1317, due to the the designation seen on the concept art pictured on the right."}
{"id": "4636", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4636", "title": "Super Earth Legion", "text": "The Super Earth Legion was the precursor to the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldiver Corps&lt;/a&gt;, and comprised of a formidable force of Legionnaires adorned in uniforms now deemed antiquated by the era of the Second Galactic War. In contrast to its successor, the Super Earth Legion was noted for its comparatively subdued sense of patriotism."}
