{"id": "3357", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3357", "title": "Trooper", "text": "\"Troopers are little more than guns with legs, base caricatures of consciousness fused to machine guns and rocket launchers. Unlike &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, the bots seem to believe that strapping heavy weaponry to expendable cannon fodder is the solution to every problem.\"\nThe primary infantry unit of the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; forces, the Trooper is the most basic Automaton unit that can be fielded in larger number and can be equipped veritable number of equipment or weapon based on mission parameters. They are considered the cannon fodder of the Automaton forces as they're the easiest to eliminate when in small numbers, however, still remain a high priority due to their ability to &lt;a href=\"Spawn%20Mechanics\"&gt;call for heavier reinforcements&lt;/a&gt;.\nThey can be divided into eight types: \nAppearance.\nThe Basic Automaton Troopers such as Raiders, Brawler and Rocket Raiders have grey colored bodies with white heads with glowing red eyes, they stand just about the same height as a Helldiver. Automaton Maruaders and MG Raiders have additional armor and maroon colored heads, with MG Raiders wearing Black backpacks with red heat sinks.\nThreat Elimination.\nTroopers and the variants aren\u2019t major threats, but they can all call in Bot Drops, so taking them out first is recommended to prevent reinforcements from arriving."}
