{"id": "3453", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3453", "title": "Troost", "text": "Troost is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The planet once housed an automaton long-range communications array, the capture of which would reveal critical intelligence about the enemy's plans.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Expeditions.\nTroost had been a peaceful planet colony of Super Earth for at least 100 years, without any happenings of note occurring before 2184 as its colonists toiled happily among the ashen trees and parasitic flowers. However, the Automatons were only programmed to hate things such as peace and freedom and, as such, launched a cowardly attack upon Troost. On February, a massive Automaton force would invade the Western Galactic Rim and take over many planets in the Xzar and Severin Sectors, Troost being among the first to fall.\nThe colonial defenses fought hard, but were no match for the robotic tide that fell onto them. Shortly after making planetfall, the Automatons would occupy Troost and install an abominable communications array to further spread their mechanized horror across the Severin Sector.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nFollowing the successful liberation of Troost during the first phase of operation Swift Disassembly, the Automaton communications array was decommissioned. Strangely however, it appeared that the array was broadcasting outside of the Galactic Frontier. Super Earth's intelligence analysts salvaged what they could to determine more, but unfortunately much of the data was already deleted.\nOne transmission that was salvaged however did contain the blueprints for a new Automaton type: &lt;a href=\"Gunship\"&gt;aerial gunships&lt;/a&gt;. Thanks to this advanced warning, the hardworking factory laborers of Super Earth were able to accelerate production of new anti-air weapons.\nOnly weeks after the liberation of Troost was it discovered that the Automatons were communicating with their main fleet, which was preparing a surprise invasion of the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nWhat many failed to realize at the time was that Troost was a warning for what was to come. Nevertheless, the Helldivers carried on with their righteous quest for freedom, crushing the Automaton forces after a decisive battle at &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;. However, this would not be the last Super Earth would see of the robots.\nA mere 3 days after their victory, the Automatons would return en masse, with a force 10 times larger than the one encountered prior. They would swiftly conquer Cyberstan and the Valdis Sector and then began to invade all the adjacent planets.\nAs the Helldivers scrambled back towards the Automaton front, the robots' advance would be halted at the Menkent-Lesath line, forcing them to search for a flank through Marfark, which would fail. After failing to flank the Menkent Line, the Automatons turned West and South, their aims refocused on regaining their old lands.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nAs the months progressed, the Automatons inched towards the Xzar sector more and more, one planet at a time, getting closer and closer to Troost. It wouldn't be long before they then captured &lt;a href=\"Choepessa%20IV\"&gt;Choepessa IV&lt;/a&gt; and returned to the Severin Sector, now through the planets that they hadn't touched before. While the Helldivers managed to secure victories in the Severin Sector, such as the destruction of the Petafactory and the capturing of Database One, the Automatons continued to push into the Severin sector nevertheless, eventually retaking &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; and then, on June 9th, Ustotu. Then, on June 22nd, the Automaton force on Ustotu launched an assault onto Vandalon IV then began to launch assaults into the Xzar Sector, prompting the SEAF to redirect all their forces towards it in order to prevent the Automatons from regaining Malevelon Creek.\nWhile the Automatons were successfully repelled, they would consolidate their defenses and capture Troost on June 25th, putting it under their control once more.\nOperation Lighthouse.\nHowever, the Automatons at Troost would not get to enjoy the recovery of their old communications array. Some weeks after the lockdown of the Xzar sector, the Helldivers would manage to score a number of key victories that culminated in Operation Andromeda, which severed the Automaton front in half. As June and August passed, the robot territories west of Cyberstan would be slowly and methodically recovered by Super Earth, with the only setback being the delayed liberation of &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt;, which resulted in the failure of Operation Liberty Crush.\nBy August 10th, Troost and Vandalon IV stood as the only remaining vestiges of the Automaton presence in the Western Galactic Rim. As such, the Helldivers were ordered to put an end to this pocket of mechanized tyranny and socialism. After Vandalon IV was liberated on August 12th, the Helldivers would immediately redirect towards Troost, which had been seeing small scale fighting since the start of the operation. Then, on August 14th, Troost would be finally liberated, delivering a crushing blow to the Automatons from which they still have not recovered.\nTopography.\nIn terms of topography, Troost is very similar to &lt;a href=\"Penta\"&gt;Penta&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Nivel%2043\"&gt;Nivel 43&lt;/a&gt; in terms of both plant life and geography. Interestingly all three planets are even home to similar species of violet flowers that grow from strange, parasitic outcroppings; whether there is some sort of correlation is currently under investigation by Federation scientists. The Automatons likely choose Troost as their communications hub because of it's location on the edge of the galactic rim, as well as it's grey fog covered surface more easily concealing the automatons facilities from orbital observation. An assumption which cost them dearly..."}
{"id": "6561", "revid": "31024592", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6561", "title": "Truth Enforcers", "text": "Truth Enforcers, released on October 31st 2024, is the eighth Premium &lt;a href=\"Warbonds\"&gt;Warbond&lt;/a&gt; available in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. Like the other Premium Warbonds, it has three pages and cost 1000 &lt;a href=\"Currencies%23Super%20Credits\"&gt;Super Credits&lt;/a&gt; to unlock.\n&lt;br&gt;\n\"Click highlighted images for details\"\n&lt;br&gt;\nto Unlock All Pages\nto Complete Warbond\nPAGE 1.\n&lt;br&gt;\nPage 2.\n&lt;br&gt;\nPage 3.\n&lt;br&gt;"}
{"id": "3263", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3263", "title": "Turing", "text": "Turing is one of the four planets that reside in the &lt;a href=\"Umlaut%20Sector\"&gt;Umlaut Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Its general landscape consists of heavy forests and rocky plateaus, with occasional large lakes. The planet is also home to the Galaxy's leading Xenoentomology Center, where Super Earth's leading Terminid experts and FTL engineers from across the galaxy converge to begin development of High-Efficiency Alcubiere Drives.\nTopography.\nTuring is characterized by its vibrant, colorful plant life. Much of the planet's surface is covered in purplish grasses, which release large amounts of pollen into the air. Its trees are divided between taller purple varieties and shorter red varieties. Citizens are reminded that recreational photography is restricted on the Barrier Planets, as of Statue C-30817.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nDeployment of the Terminid Control System.\nTuring was briefly a frontline planet from the 14th of February to the 23rd. A Terminid outbreak occurred in the area on March 6th, causing fighting to resume until the 14th of March. Fighting ended with the establishment of the &lt;a href=\"Terminid%20Control%20System\"&gt;Terminid Control System&lt;/a&gt; on the planet. Turing was not considered a strategically important world at this point, allowing the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;fascist Terminid pest&lt;/a&gt; on her surface to persist unchecked for far too long. \nFailure of the Terminid Control System.\nOn April 29th, Operation Legitimate Undertaking was interrupted by massive Terminid outbreaks in the Umlaut sector, including on Turing. A malfunction in the TCS allowed the bugs to reproduce at a much higher rate, turning the neighboring planet &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; into a Supercolony. The Helldivers were quickly deployed to deactivate the TCS throughout the Umlaut Sector. On May 3rd, the TCS on Turing was shut down, preventing it from meeting the same tragic fate as Meridia. However, its close proximity to the Supercolony left it at constant risk of assault.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOn May 21, 2184, after the declaration of the Second Galactic War, the Terminids launched another brutal assault against Turing. The Helldivers were dispatched here and heroically routed the enemy by day's end. On May 24th, another assault was launched. Unfortunately, with Helldivers' attention being split between &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture&lt;/a&gt;, local defense forces were overrun by the tyrannical bugs, who quickly re-occupied the planet. The very next day, Operation Enduring Peace was announced to retake Turing and establish a foothold toward liberating Meridia. \nOperation Enduring Peace.\nTo properly deal with Meridia, the SEAF retook and defended Turing, along with Angel's Venture and &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt;. On June 1st, with progress on destroying &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridia&lt;/a&gt; well underway, the Terminids launched an opportunistic strike on Turing. The Defense of Turing began on June 1st, with ~10,000 Helldivers being dispatched here, and another ~3,500 fighting on nearby &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;. Though the Terminids' tyrannical methods allowed them to gain the upper hand, the USAF was able to control the planet for long enough to provide a temporary foothold toward Meridia. Operation Enduring Peace came to an end with the collapse of Meridia into a black hole using &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Fluid\"&gt;Dark Fluid&lt;/a&gt; technology. \nOperation Destiny Manifested.\nWith the Meridia Supercolony being permanently destroyed, the SEAF was ordered to take back nearby contested planets: Turing, &lt;a href=\"Erata%20Prime\"&gt;Erata Prime&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Phact%20Bay\"&gt;Phact Bay&lt;/a&gt;. Turing was the first planet to be liberated in this successful operation, allowing Super Earth citizens to finally resettle the lands they had been forced to abandon. \nOperation Glorious Xenocide.\nTuring was briefly attacked on July 21st. The Helldivers held the line valiantly and turned the Terminid assault around, now forcing them back to Acamar IV and then, on July 23rd, back to Gacrux. \nOperation Alcubierre-II.\nFollowing the last assault onto Turing, it spent the rest of the summer of 2184 in relative peace, as the Terminids shifted focus towards the rest of the Jin Xi Sector. With the apparition of the Gloom, most threats to Turing's security were gone, as the planets within the Gloom that could have posed a threat seemingly stopped attacking its neighbors. However, the threat at Gacrux still remained. After Acamar IV fell on September 25th, Turing would immediately be attacked by the Terminids, just as Super Earth ordered the construction of a new Xenoentomology Center on the planet.\nAs such, the Helldivers were ordered to defend and hold Turing while construction was underway, as this new center would help make the Alcubierre Warp Drive of the Super Destroyers more efficient in its E-710 consumption. As such, the Helldivers deployed en masse once more onto the planet, holding the line from September 27th to September 29th, successfully driving back the insectoid menace.\nTuring would be successfully defended on September 26th. However, due to its newly found relevance in relation to the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt;, the Terminids would make huge efforts to invade the planet in order to impede the construction of the Xenoentomology Center. After they amassed their forces following their defeat at Achird III, the Terminids would launch a second final assault from Acamar IV once more on October 2nd. However, this time, the Helldivers would not only successfully rally at &lt;a href=\"Turing\"&gt;Turing&lt;/a&gt; and deliver a crippling blow to the fascist bugs, but they would also wind up liberating &lt;a href=\"Acamar%20IV\"&gt;Acamar IV&lt;/a&gt;, cutting off a nearby source of terminid spores and setting up a defensive perimeter around the planet that, for the moment, safeguards the planet and its new xenoentomology center.\nMeanwhile the other side of the galaxy, the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; attempted to capitalize on our noble scientific efforts by assaulting &lt;a href=\"Mastia\"&gt;Mastia&lt;/a&gt; intending to cut off the &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;DSS Logistics Hub&lt;/a&gt; from the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;DSS&lt;/a&gt; itself. But the Helldivers quickly organized a daring counterattack, saving Mastia and liberating &lt;a href=\"Shelt\"&gt;Shelt&lt;/a&gt; in the process.\nThanks to these valiant efforts, ground has been broken on the new Xenoentomology Center on Turing. Super Earth's leading Terminid experts and FTL engineers from across the galaxy have converged on the planet to begin development of High-Efficiency Alcubiere Drives. These new drives will enable the &lt;a href=\"Democracy%20Space%20Station\"&gt;Democracy Space Station&lt;/a&gt; to warp between planets at the Helldivers' direction, dispensing Freedom wherever it is needed. Research and development of this new technology will take weeks, during which time the center must remain safe from Terminid infestation, or our research progress will be lost. Thanks to the valiant efforts of the Helldivers, all of humanity will soon step forward into a more prosperous, energy efficient, and peaceful future.\nOperation Spark of Liberty.\nTuring would remain free of any Terminid presence after the construction of the Xenoentomology Center concluded. It would seem that, after all, things hadn't come to boil, even after the severe tactical miscalculation at &lt;a href=\"Gacrux\"&gt;Gacrux&lt;/a&gt; during Operation Crossroads. But the seeds of fascism had already been sown on the Terminid Research Preserve, and it was only a matter of time before their bore their nefarious fruits.\nOn November 12th, in the middle of a busy day for the Tyranny Park, a massive underground Terminid hive erupted spontaneously, leading to a bloody massacre of visitors and park staff alike. Acamar IV was overrun in mere minutes, which prevented the nuclear security measures from being activated and allowed the Terminids to take over the planet without any impediment. Once Acamar IV fell, it launched 5 simultaneous attacks onto all of the planets connected to it. This catastrophe could not have been any more poorly timed, as the Jet Brigade had also just returned in massive numbers and destroyed the DSS Logistics Hub on &lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe painting was clear on the wall that the Helldivers had to act quick before more damage had to be done. Despite Acamar's positioning, High Command gave the indication to protect the Xenoentomology Center at Turing by all means, as it still contained critical research material on the Terminids, pretty much dooming Acamar IV and all of its attached planets to perdition.\nAfter 16 hours of fighting, Turing was saved, at the expense of losing not just Acamar but also all the other planets connected to it except for Turing. With the Jet Brigade approaching Mastia, the final nail in the coffin was put, with 3 months of sacrifices being lost as the Borgus Sector fell back to Terminid control, while the Jin Xi sector's liberation was pretty much undone."}
