{"id": "3667", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3667", "title": "Ustotu", "text": "Ustotu is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nUstotu is similar to Erata Prime, being a sandy desert with unstable tectonic activity.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Expedition.\nDuring the month of February 2184, a surprise attack by a large &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton&lt;/a&gt; Force would see the planets on the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Galactic Rim&lt;/a&gt; under attack by a massive robot force. As the defenses in Mantes and Draupnir fell and the Automatons encroached further and further into the Galactic Rim, they eventually advanced onto Ustotu.\nIt would be here where their advances would be stopped, as the Helldivers began to gain momentum and forced the Automatons to divert their resources towards Tien Kwan, a fruitless endeavor that ultimately paved the way for the robot's demise. Ustotu would be caught in the crossfire between the Helldivers and the Automatons, being stuck in a liberation campaign for months.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nAs the bots began losing ground and the Helldivers approached the Xzar and Severin Sectors, the Automatons withdrew. With the liberation of Troost, their offensive in Ustotu would be crippled, as they had lost the FTL Line that allowed them to stay supplied. Ustotu and Vandalon IV would be liberated shortly after.\nUstotu would remain under the stewardship of Super Earth for the remainder of the operation, with its colonists joyously celebrating the victory at Malevelon Creek and the righteous eradication of the Automatons at Malevelon Creek.\nBut peace was to be short-lived. A mere 3 days after their grandiose victory, the Automatons returned, taking over the Valdis Sector and rapidly advancing through the neighboring Andromeda Sector.\nThe Second Galactic War had begun\nSecond Galactic War.\nAs the bots were contained in the Menkent Line, they would withdraw into defensive positions, consolidating their defenses around the planets immediately adjacent to the &lt;a href=\"Valdis%20Sector\"&gt;Valdis Sector&lt;/a&gt;, with neighboring Varylia 5 and Choepessa IV falling into the enemies' mechanical hands. However, as the war progressed and the Helldivers encircled them, the bots would begin making attempts to break out of the Valdis sector and expand their territories, by making daring raids throughout the Trigon Sector. In early May, they attempted to jump out of &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt; and into the Xzar Sector through &lt;a href=\"Mort\"&gt;Mort&lt;/a&gt; but were successfully repelled, leading them to concentrate their advance on the planets connected to Choepessa IV. \nWhile seeing some initial success, with their advances into Varylia 5 and into the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt; being mostly successful, they would be quickly halted and their successes reversed after Operation Emancipator returned Varylia 5 to the Helldivers, which then forced the bots to attack the only other planet that was connected to Choepessa IV: Ustotu \nDefense of Ustotu (June 9th - June 10th).\nThe Automatons would return to Ustotu on evening of June 9th, 2184. Due to Major Orders from High Command enforicing the focus on &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt;, the planet would end up falling by the next day, getting trapped in a deadlock.\nShortly after, as the Helldivers were ordered back into the Terminid Front and then focused on defending the Xzar Sector, the Automatons launched an assault onto Troost. Once Troost's defenses collapsed, both it and Ustotu would be lost for good, as the bots would shortly recover Varylia 5 after a successful assault from Choepessa IV overwhelmed its defenses.\nOperation Liberty Crush.\nUstotu remained under Automaton occupation throughout the month of June and into July. However, its chance at liberation would appear from an unlikely source. After securing the plans for the intergalactic battle station at X-45, the Automaton Front would be split in half after the success of Operation Righteous Expunge. With Ustotu now cut away from its supply lines to Cyberstan, the order was issued for the liberation of all planets within the encirclement zone. Once Choepessa was liberated on July 28th, some Helldivers would divert towards Ustotu to assist local resistance efforts in order to thwart possible counteroffensives. \nThen, on July 31st, shortly after victory at Varylia 5, the main force of the Helldivers began to arrive at Ustotu. The battle would be fierce and lengthy, which would buy the Automaton garrison at Wezen time to fortify its defenses. Victory would be achieved at the late hours of August 1st after almost a full day of fighting, which ultimately made Operation Liberty Crush fail."}
{"id": "3322", "revid": "55838822", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3322", "title": "Valdis Sector", "text": "The Valdis Sector is a sector found on the &lt;a href=\"Western%20Front\"&gt;Western Front&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Helldivers%202\"&gt;Helldivers 2&lt;/a&gt;. It consists of 6 planets, which would all be the targets of the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; main invasion fleet during the \"Reclamation.\"\nWhilst their interests in the sector are still currently unknown, what is known is that they hit the SEAF defenders hard and fast, overrunning every planet in a matter of hours. First by attacking communications networks to delay the deployment of SEAF and Helldiver forces, then warping in a massive fleet from deep space, before assaulting the planets with a ground force ten times the size of the legion destroyed in the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nWhile the Sector has been temporarily occupied by the maleficent robots, its liberation is imminent. It may not be today. It may not be tomorrow. But the Valdis Sector will be liberated."}
