{"id": "5946", "revid": "37419324", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5946", "title": "Valmox", "text": "Valmox is one of the seven planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Rictus%20Sector\"&gt;Rictus Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Gatria\"&gt;Gatria&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ubanea\"&gt;Ubanea&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Crimsica\"&gt;Crimsica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Ingmar\"&gt;Ingmar&lt;/a&gt;. Valmox is a rugged and striking world, slightly smaller than &lt;a href=\"Super%20Earth\"&gt;Super Earth&lt;/a&gt;, the ecosystem of Valmox is characterized by treeless flat steppes, gently rolling hills, wetlands, and interlinkages with several continent spanning Mountain Range. Whilst it might appear from orbit that much of the surface is covered in crimson red grass, this grass is in reality a crimson algae that has propagated wildly across the entire planet.\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nReturn of the Illuminate.\nValmox was, for much of its recorded history, a peaceful planet colony of the Federation of Super Earth that, by all standards, was pretty uneventful. Having been settled at some during the Great Democratization after the First Galactic War, the first colonists possibly found a naturally resource-rich and fertile region in which to settle. This resulted in the colonists congregating into more in fortified communities over time, which ultimately developed into the planet's first true cities, complete with working appliances, services such as electricity and waste management and many other staples of urban living.\nHowever, an old foe of Managed Democracy dedicated themselves to staring at Valmox with envy from deep within the endless vastness of space. The , once thought defeated and extinct, had returned and were once again determined to wage war against Freedom.\nOn December 17th, Valmox was attacked in tandem with &lt;a href=\"Kerth%20Secundus\"&gt;Kerth Secundus&lt;/a&gt;, another planet colony in another sector. However, Valmox's hopes were not lost as the Helldivers, who had already defeated the Illuminate before at &lt;a href=\"Calypso\"&gt;Calypso&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Bellatrix\"&gt;Bellatrix&lt;/a&gt;, were determined to end this odious stalking of Valmox's noble citizenry once and for all. For almost 8 hours, the Helldivers valiantly held the line at Valmox while the invaders at Kerth were repelled. Then, once Kerth Secundus had been rescued, the Helldiver Corps concentrated on Valmox and cast the alien invaders away, safeguarding its citizens and settlements once again."}
{"id": "3396", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3396", "title": "Vandalon IV", "text": "Vandalon IV is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;. It's covered in large glaciers and rivers of thick ice.\nTopography.\nAn arctic planet far away from it's own star, Vandalon IV is a world which is submerged in eternal winter, the frosty peaks of the worlds mountains and massive continent sized glaciers. Purposeful terraforming efforts by the federation as well as the industry of Automaton factories have warmed the planet enough that the ice has started to melt, creating several large oceans, though the water is still too cold to safely swim in. Colonists still need to wear extra layers of clothing when going outside, whilst intense snow storms are an almost daily occurrence.\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nOperation Swift Disassembly.\nPhase One.\nDuring first phase of operation Swift Disassembly, &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt;, which was lying deeper within Trigon Sector was deemed an important Long-Range Communication Array. With Vandalon laying on the FTL path to it, it was quickly liberated shortly after &lt;a href=\"Ustotu\"&gt;Ustotu&lt;/a&gt; on March 28th, 2184.\nPhase Four.\nDuring the late Operation Swift Disassembly, the Automatons probably discovered a new Route directly to Vandalon IV resulting in a swift attack while many &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; were focusing on holding the ground of &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ubanea\"&gt;Ubanea&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt; as well as attacking the remaining Automaton planets. While most Helldivers underestimated the importance of Vandalon IV as a planet that was now a barrier between the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;, a few Helldivers engaged in a swift and bloody fight on the Planet.\nWhile the fight looked like a loss, many Helldivers fought brave against the Automatons without receiving much reinforcements from the other frontlines. While many Helldivers weren't able to see how important Vandalon IV was, the remaining troops and inhabitants on Vandalon IV, stood strong together. In a bloody fight they were able to defend the planet successfully in a very narrow victory and thus secured the last phase of the Operation Swift Disassembly. This planet suffered the last attack by the Automatons prior to their attack on the Northwestern region of the galaxy.\nBy April 9th, Vandalon IV and the surrounding systems were safe, sound and in the tender care of Managed Democracy.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Xzar Lockdown.\nDuring operation Xzar Lockdown, Automaton invasion fleet has made planetfall on Vandalon, while most of helldivers were busy securing &lt;a href=\"Mort\"&gt;Mort&lt;/a&gt; in Xzar Sector. Control over planet was declared lost shortly after midnight of June 23rd, after which the Automatons launched a surprise assault onto &lt;a href=\"Mantes\"&gt;Mantes&lt;/a&gt; through a newly opened FTL supply line. \nThen, immediately after Mantes' defense had succeeded, they launched a second assault onto Ingmar on the late hours of June 23rd, with said assault also being repealed by the morning of June 24th.\nSuper Earth Tactical Command deems Vandalon IV a second-tier priority target, as its position allows the Automatons to easily throw concurrent assaults at the Xzar Sector and, given the newly discovered capabilities of the enemy, puts them right at the doorsteps of &lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;. It is highly advised that, unless ordered elsewhere, Helldivers prioritize its liberation.\nOn July 17th, with the success of Operation Andromeda, this planet, alongside all planets in the Ymir, Trigon and Andromeda Sectors, has seen its defenses collapse, meaning that no liberation progress will be undone.. or so we thought.\nHowever, on July 23rd, a strategic update was rolled out, announcing that the automatons have rapidly began repairing their communications and forces, therefore increasing their defenses and resistance again. This caused the liberation rate to begin declining again as the decay rate became enough to overpower the little forces fighting on the planet. With the liberation of Ustotu incoming as of August 1st, there won't be many planets left in the cut-off forces anymore. Let us hope that this brings the final liberation of this illegally held world upon us soon..\nOperation Liberty Crush.\nAfter their victory at &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;, the Helldivers would manage to secure a defensive line of planets that split the bot front in half, with Vandalon IV being within the encircled domain. As such, Super Earth High Command issued an order for the immediate recapture of five of the encircled planets. Although Vandalon IV was not one of the key targets of the operation and the major order was an overall failure due to the &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt; being captured behind schedule.\nHowever the successful capture of Wezen and defence of &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt; following the operation, meant that both the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda&lt;/a&gt; Sectors are once again securely in Super Earths hands. High Command's strategy of dividing the bot forces is now a firm reality, with only &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; still in automaton clutches in the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Whilst the Automaton's may have won the battle, the Super Earth Armed Forces are well on their way to winning the war.\nOperation Lighthouse.\nVandalon IV would be completely cut off from Cyberstan after Operation Liberty Crush. As such, it and Troost represented the only remaining vestiges of Automaton power in the old territories that they once occupied. As such, the Helldivers were order to finally squash this last pocket of Automaton resistance once and for all. Vandalon IV would be liberated by the Helldivers on August 12th, after 2 days or arduous fighting over the frozen planet, Troost would follow, being liberated on August 14th, marking the complete destruction of the Automaton Encirclement."}
