{"id": "4578", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4578", "title": "Varylia 5", "text": "Varylia 5 is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;. The planet was unremarkable until it was discovered that the Automaton's were building a massive factory on the planet, which the Super Earth Armed Forces were able to capture and modify into a second Morgunson Arsenal; used to build the new &lt;a href=\"EXO-49%20Emancipator%20Exosuit\"&gt;EXO-49 Emancipator Exosuit&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nVarylia 5 is a planet covered in barren grassy plains and rocky hills, blanketed by perpetual fog and prone to torrential rainstorms. Due to it's distance from Super Earth and it's previously hostile nature, Varylia 5 was sparsely populated and even more sparsely defended even before the outbreak of the Second Galactic War. As a result, it was captured by the Automatons early, only being liberated in the first phase of operation swift disassembly.\nHowever this has not been the first time that the planet has felt the bootstrap of socialist tyranny as one hundred years ago, the planet was one of the many occupied by the . Back then, Varylia was a very hostile world, plagued by a scorching environment, plagued by geological instability which caused mantle to bubble up from the planets core to create seas of magma that cover most of the surface. Even so, the parts of the planet that weren't covered in lava were incredibly fertile, with some supporting small islands of vibrant green plant life in the form of shrubs and grasses. Some Helldivers even reported burned trees and the bleached skeletons of animals, perhaps suggesting that Varylia 5 was not always so inhospitable.\nNever the less, following the end of the first war, the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Expansion\"&gt;Ministry of Expansion&lt;/a&gt; gained oversight over the planet and began terraforming efforts. After a century of terraforming efforts, the planet has become a lot more hospitable and geologically stable, with environmental conditions now similar to &lt;a href=\"Draupnir\"&gt;Draupnir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Matar%20Bay\"&gt;Matar Bay&lt;/a&gt;. The redirection of ice comets to cool the oceans of lava has created not only large contents of rocky basalt, but also created huge bodies of water which allowed for more plant life (and regular humans) to thrive (had the first colonies not been blown up by &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;rampaging socialist toasters&lt;/a&gt; who then built their \"Petafactory\" on the ruins, polluting the planets once pristine atmosphere).\nNever the less, the planet still stands as a testimony to humanity's ability to tame even the harshest of planets, and will be reclaimed in the name of freedom soon...\nHistory.\nSpecial Military Operations.\nAutomaton Invasion of Cyberstan.\nVarylia would be one of the first planets to fall to the red tide that arrived during the initial invasion of Cyberstan. It would be defended successfully on April 25th, 2184, but would then fall to a second assault on May 20th.\nSecond Galactic War.\nAs the war developed, Varylia would remain relatively safe, untouched by the mechanical scourge even when left unattended amidst the Disaster of Meridia, which shook up things in the Automaton Front and forced vast amounts of troops and material away from it.\nIt wouldn't be until after the declaration of the Second Galactic War that Varylia, having been left underdefended, would tragically fall to the cybernetic menace. This time, the robots would show their true plans for the planet, as they would bring their previously interrupted plans into fruition. Super Earth Intelligence scan revealed that a megafactory, called the \"Petrafactory\" by enemy transmissions was at the advanced stages of its construction, with goals for it still unknown. Analysts noted a particular resemblance to the Morguson Armories in Tien Kwan, which could indicate that the robots, sapping the cunning and hard work of the citizens of Super Earth as usual, had decided to undertake the endeavor of creating superweapons of unknown nature.\nOperation Emancipator.\nWith time running out, Super Earth High Command, shortly after the failure of Operation Freedom's Calling, would issue a major order for the immediate liberation of Varylia 5 and its \"Petafactories\", in order to repurpose them for the mass production of EXO-49 Dual-Autocannon Emancipator Exosuits. No sooner had the first SEAF standard issue boots set foot on Varylia 5's soil then did fresh intel warn of an increased level of Automaton resistance, likely a last-ditch effort to forestall their inevitable defeat.\nNever the less after a day of some of the heaviest Automaton resistance in the war so far (5%), the Helldivers had managed to make a foothold on the planet for the Super Earth Armed Forces, though were unable to push forward much further. However it was then that the &lt;a href=\"Ministry%20of%20Intelligence\"&gt;Ministry of Intelligence&lt;/a&gt; reported that spore activity on the &lt;a href=\"Meridia\"&gt;Meridian Supercolony&lt;/a&gt; had abruptly increased within the last 24 hours, with sudden Terminid outbreaks occurring on previously-safe planets as a result (yet more evidence of a Bug-Bot conspiracy). One such planet was &lt;a href=\"Angel%27s%20Venture\"&gt;Angel's Venture,&lt;/a&gt; which if overrun would result in the loss of the valuable, newly-constructed SEAF Training Facility on the planet, which will significantly decrease the capability of the Super Earth Armed Forces to aid in galactic defense.\nThus Super Earth High Command recommended the prioritization of the defense of Angel's Venture over the offensive on Varylia 5, with the Helldivers being redirected to the planet. After Angel's Venture was saved, the Helldivers returned to Varylia 5 where the Automaton resistance had been worn down significantly (from 5% to 3.5%). On May 26th, 2184, the planet was liberated from the toasters' grasp. When the first Super-Earth engineers arrived at the Petrafactory, it was discovered with great horror that the working conditions were abhorrent (even by Bot standards), with millions of cramped Automaton drones working endlessly in an unsafe factory environent to produce weapons for the Socialist war machine. Well-compensated Super-Earth engineers, as of this writing, are hard at work retrofitting the Petrafactory to produce Emancipator Exosuits.\nOperation Liberty Crush.\nVarylia 5 would not remain under Super Earth's embrace for long. shortly after Operation Emancipator concluded, Operation Enduring Peace commenced on the Eastern Front in order to put an end to the Meridian Supercolony Crisis, which had spread beyond all tolerable thresholds. As the war progressed into June, Varylia's defenses would remain pulled away from their garrison and into other operations, which allowed the Automatons to launch an assault on the planet and retake it in the early weeks of July prior to Operation Xzar Lockdown.\nHowever, not all would be lost for Varylia. Shortly after their victory at X-45 during Operation Starslayer and Operation Andromeda, the Automaton Front would be severed in half, with the occupying bot garrison in Varylia being cut off from their supply line to Cyberstan. Immediately, the order was given to recapture all of the planets within the encirclement zone, which opened the way for Varylia's liberation. As Operation Righteous Expunge forced the tin man's fist out of its forward bases at &lt;a href=\"Charbal-VII\"&gt;Charbal-VII&lt;/a&gt; and Choepessa, scattered fighting began to take place in Varylia, as Helldivers returned to support what little resistance fighters they could. However, the real battle for Varylia 5 would begin on July 29th, once Vega Bay had been retaken from the Automatons.\nThe battle would be fierce and lengthy, requiring the entirety of the day of July 30th. Progress was slow, and the newly installed &lt;a href=\"Automaton%20Orbital%20Cannons\"&gt;Automaton Orbital Cannons&lt;/a&gt; made it more difficult to support the ground efforts. But nevertheless, the Helldivers came out victorious over the socialist machines, successfully expelling them off Varylia on the afternoon of July 31st."}
{"id": "5226", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5226", "title": "Vega Bay", "text": " is one of the 5 planets in the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;. \nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Heeth\"&gt;Heeth&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vog-Sojoth\"&gt;Vog-Sojoth&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Destiny Manifested.\nFirst Battle of Vega Bay (June 2nd-3rd).\nVega Bay would be a peaceful planet for most of the initial months of the Second Galactic War. However, peace was not to last. On June 2nd, 2184, shortly after the conclusion of Operation Enduring Peace, Automaton Forces in &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt; launched an assault at Vega Bay, in pursuit of their goal of kicking the SEAF out of the Ymir Sector and ultimately enlarge their entrenchment into the Western Galactic Rim. By June 3rd, Vega Bay had fallen to the Automaton assaults and the liberation campaign failed due to FTL lines to &lt;a href=\"Vega%20Bay\"&gt;Vega Bay&lt;/a&gt; being cut off.\nOperation Valiant Resistance.\nSecond Battle of Vega Bay (June 8th-9th).\nAfter the liberation of &lt;a href=\"Wezen\"&gt;Wezen&lt;/a&gt;, Helldivers flooded to Vega Bay, as it was next in the route to Wasat, the location of the rumored Database one, an important Automaton Datacenter. Progress was swift, with the indomitable might of the &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; crushing the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; stationed here. At 10pm Earth Super Time the last &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; on this planet were scrapped, &lt;a href=\"Helldivers\"&gt;Helldivers&lt;/a&gt; were quick to move to the Automaton world of &lt;a href=\"Wasat\"&gt;Wasat&lt;/a&gt;, The home of Database One.\nOperation Starslayer.\nThird Battle of Vega Bay (July 5th-8th ).\nOperation Starslayer began on July 3rd. Automaton forces scrambled to make counterattacks aimed at cutting off reinforcements to the &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X system&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Meissa\"&gt;Meissa system&lt;/a&gt;. Vega bay, being part of the supply line connecting the Ymir Sector to the rest of Super Earth's space, became a target of interest for the socialist machines. \nA defense campaign began on July 5th to hold the system. Due to it's strategic importance, Vega Bay received more reinforcement than the neighbouring systems, which ultimately decided the fate of this defensive campaign. However, a second assault followed on July 6th, which would not enjoy as much aid. This inevitably led to Vega Bay falling on July 7th.\nOperation Liberty Crush.\nFourth Battle of Vega Bay.\nFor 3 weeks, Vega Bay remained in a bloody stalemate between the Helldivers and the Automatons, as the Helldivers had to jump back to the Terminid Front then towards the Hydra and Lacaille Sectors. However, with Operation Andromeda, the Automaton front was severed in half, leaving Vega Bay disconnected from Cyberstan, with its defenses in disarray. Before it could recover, the Helldivers would send the main fleet towards it, seeking to open the line towards Wezen. By July 30th, Vega Bay had been finally liberated once and for all, with the Automatons being squeezed out of the Ymir Sector on August 4th with the liberation of Wezen, ensuring Vega Bay would remain free for good."}
