{"id": "3673", "revid": "1524681", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=3673", "title": "Weapons", "text": "List of all weapons.\n&lt;tabber&gt;\n&lt;/tabber&gt;\nOverview.\nPrimary and secondary weapons can be equipped before deploying to combat, though Primary weapons can also be picked up in the field. Helldivers can also equip one type of grenade, these cannot be swapped in the field. Whenever a Helldiver deploys to the field, they will be supplied with their chosen loadout and most of the respective ammo capacity (or full capacity with the &lt;a href=\"Boosters\"&gt;Hellpod Space Optimization&lt;/a&gt; booster).\nStratagem or Support Weapons are not provided in the standard loadout and must be called in with their respective Stratagem (though they can also be randomly found in the field). They have their own weapon slot, so any Helldiver can carry one in addition to the rest of their loadout. Unlike the other weapons, they are effectively lost on death and may be lost behind enemy lines until their stratagem comes off cooldown. This can also somewhat limit their available ammunition, though they can still get ammo from all the usual sources, such as the &lt;a href=\"Resupply\"&gt;Resupply&lt;/a&gt; stratagem (though only half the reserve capacity by default). They also aren't deployed with full reserve capacity by default. In both cases there are &lt;a href=\"Ship%20Modules\"&gt;Ship Module&lt;/a&gt; upgrades available to provide full capacity.\nAmmunition.\nEvery weapon has its own ammunition type and number of reserve mags/rounds (or heat sinks for laser weapons) a Helldiver can carry at once. Remaining ammunition in a weapon cannot be transferred, even if picked up while already carrying the exact same weapon. Reloading magazine-based weapons will always discard any ammo left in the current magazine, so it should be avoided unless its close to empty or easy opportunity to stock up is close at hand. The amount of ammo in each magazine also depends on the weapon itself and can range from marksman rifles with a few rounds each to rapid-fire machine guns with hundreds. A few weapons reload single rounds or partial capacity through clips.\nEnergy-based weapons have a lot of variation when it comes to their ammunition mechanics, and can be grouped into three types; plasma, laser and arc. \nPlasma weapons, such as the &lt;a href=\"PLAS-1%20Scorcher\"&gt;PLAS-1 Scorcher&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"SG-8P%20Punisher%20Plasma\"&gt;SG-8P Punisher Plasma&lt;/a&gt; function essentially the same as standard weapons, relying on a set amount of cartridges that have a set number of shots each. \nLaser weapons like the &lt;a href=\"LAS-5%20Scythe\"&gt;LAS-5 Scythe&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"LAS-98%20Laser%20Cannon\"&gt;LAS-98 Laser Cannon&lt;/a&gt; rely on heatsinks in order to fire, the more you fire the more heat builds up. If you stop firing before the heat builds up too much, the weapon will cool down until the heat meter depletes or you start firing again, but if the heat meter reaches 100% your weapon will stop firing and you will need to replace your heatsink. The only laser weapon that does not rely on heatsinks is the &lt;a href=\"LAS-99%20Quasar%20Cannon\"&gt;LAS-99 Quasar Cannon&lt;/a&gt;, which shoots an explosive projectile rather than a beam and needs to charge up each shot and cool down afterwards.\nArc weapons, which are currently limited to the &lt;a href=\"ARC-3%20Arc%20Thrower\"&gt;ARC-3 Arc Thrower&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"ARC-12%20Blitzer\"&gt;ARC-12 Blitzer&lt;/a&gt;, seem to be some of the few weapons with truly infinite ammo, but also have both a limited rate of fire and low effective range as a tradeoff. While they don't rely on ammunition, they both have somewhat unique firing mechanics; the Arc Thrower needs each shot to be charged up for about a second before firing each shot, while the Blitzer technically fires automatically with a 1.5 second cooldown between shots.\nSome support weapons do not carry reserve ammo by themselves and require a special backpack (supplied alongside the weapon) to carry it instead. These can be carried by another player, if they are willing to remain close and provide a team reload as needed.\nDespite these limitations, sources of ammunition resupply are generally universal. Ammunition can be picked up from boxes found on the map, the &lt;a href=\"Resupply\"&gt;Resupply&lt;/a&gt; Pod or Supply Pack, which will automatically supply reserve ammo for every weapon (or ammo backpack) the Helldiver is currently carrying. This won't refill the currently loaded magazine however, and the source of ammunition is entirely used up, even if it only supplies a single item. Reloading weapons before picking up ammunition is generally preferable. Primary and secondary weapons always get their full reserve capacity back, Support weapons only get half without a specific ship module upgrade; superior packing methodology. Boxes found on the map work a bit differently and only provide a single magazine (or heat sink) for all weapons at the same time, including Support weapons. \nAmmunition is also a factor at play for most Defensive stratagem deployments and Vehicles, which cannot be resupplied. Sentries will automatically deactivate when they run out of it."}
{"id": "5746", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5746", "title": "Western Front", "text": "The Western Front is a theatre of the &lt;a href=\"Second%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;Second Galactic War&lt;/a&gt; fought between the &lt;a href=\"Federation%20of%20Super%20Earth\"&gt;Federation of Super Earth&lt;/a&gt; and the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automaton Legion&lt;/a&gt;. Fighting began in early 2184 when the Automatons made several incursions into the &lt;a href=\"Severin%20Sector\"&gt;Severin Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Ever since Super Earth and the Automatons have been locked in a struggle for control over the Galactic West. \nGeneral Information.\nSectors:.\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;3,921,119,000 Automatons killed. &gt;170,042,000 Helldivers killed.\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;1,083,412,000 Automatons killed, &gt;48,221,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;347,000 Automatons killed, &gt;24,580 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;3,142,409,000 Automatons killed, &gt;118,318,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;1,884,521,000 Automatons killed, &gt;60,785,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Automaton Presence\n&lt;4,681,720,000 Automatons killed, &gt;151,972,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Automaton Control\n&gt;6,030,474,000 Automatons killed, &gt;213,550,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Automaton Presence\n&lt;3,843,415,000 Automatons killed, &gt;133,270,000 Helldivers killed\nStatus: Automaton Control\n&gt;21,214,000 Automatons Killed, &gt;929,700 Helldivers Killed\nStatus: Automaton Presence\n&gt;945,106,000 Automatons Killed, &gt;27,607,000 Helldivers Killed\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;1,403,514,000 Automatons Killed, &gt;46,452,000 Helldivers Killed\nStatus: Automaton Presence\n&gt;1,260,240,000 Automatons Killed, &gt;33,079,000 Helldivers Killed\nStatus: Super Earth Control\n&gt;77,731,000 Automatons Killed, &gt;1,589,000 Helldivers Killed\nIn total, 28.3 billion &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt; have been slain. 1 Billion Helldivers have given their lives in the crusade against socialism, along with countless S.E.A.F volunteers and civilians. It is becoming apparent that the Second Galactic War is one of the worst losses of life ever experienced in history.\nNoteable Planets / Battles.\n&lt;a href=\"Shallus\"&gt;Shallus&lt;/a&gt;: The farthest the Automatons have ever pushed into Super Earth space.\n&lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt;: The first Swamp planet on the Western Front.\n&lt;a href=\"Tarsh\"&gt;Tarsh&lt;/a&gt;: The first Foggy Swamp planet on the Western Front.\n&lt;a href=\"Malevelon%20Creek\"&gt;Malevelon Creek&lt;/a&gt;: A Shadowed Jungle planet that had seen constant fighting for 60 days - famous for its courageous defense by the Helldivers. \n&lt;a href=\"Merak\"&gt;Merak&lt;/a&gt;: The farthest the Helldivers have ever pushed towards &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;.\nSome of the most fought over planets include &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Vernen%20Wells\"&gt;Vernen Wells&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lesath\"&gt;Lesath&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Tibit\"&gt;Tibit&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Durgen\"&gt;Durgen&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Martale\"&gt;Martale&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Ubanea\"&gt;Ubanea&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "5243", "revid": "55339407", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5243", "title": "Wezen", "text": "Wezen is one of five inhabited worlds within the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Devoured by constant wildfires, it stands as the gateway into the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nTogether with other planets of its biome, Wezen features mostly mountainous terrain with narrow ravines, accompanied by occasional open plateaus. Elevation changes are rare, but once they appear they are quite steep. Any local flora consists of mostly hardy thorny shrubs, very low grasses, and colonies of exploding mushrooms.\nWeather.\nWeather conditions on Wezen are similar to other desert planets like &lt;a href=\"Hellmire\"&gt;Hellmire&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Menkent\"&gt;Menkent&lt;/a&gt;. This consists of cycling firestorms and fire tornados, followed either by complete lack of clouds or heavy ash choked fog. Expect mostly low visibility as the world burns around you, with the clear weather being an exception. Local fire tornadoes are especially lethal, following random movement patterns and are capable of incinerating anything in mere seconds. The ground itself will stay aflame in its wake, so tread carefully. The hot weather also will also worsen overheating in some weapons such as &lt;a href=\"LAS-99%20Quasar%20Cannon\"&gt;Quasar Cannons&lt;/a&gt;. \nRemember - When on fire, Drop and Roll/Stim!\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nFirst Battle of Wezen (May 23rd-24th).\nOriginally far from frontlines, this planet was theorized to be targeted for invasion by Automatons on their speculative march to &lt;a href=\"Cyberstan\"&gt;Cyberstan&lt;/a&gt;. Of course, such rumours quickly fell silent when Automatons Fleets were destroyed during Operation Swift Disassembly.\nThe planet came under direct attack on May 23, 2184, from direction of occupied &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt;. Despite heroic sacrifice of over 350 thousand helldivers, planetary defences and SEAF troops were overwhelmed shortly after noon on May 24th.\nSecond Battle of Wezen (June 7th-8th) (Operation Valiant Resistance).\nOn June 7th, 2184, High Command announced a liberation campaign against the Automaton Data Center One on planet Wasat, deeper in &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir Sector&lt;/a&gt;. Wezen was quickly identified by the Helldiver Corps as the best way to approach the target planet. The first &lt;a href=\"Super%20Destroyer\"&gt;Super Destroyers&lt;/a&gt; arrived on early afternoon of same day, however initial progress was slow but promising, enough so for High Command to send out a strategic update advising Helldivers to target Wezen. SEAF reinforcements quickly flooded in and progress was being made, with the planet being liberated on early hours of June 8th, 2184. \nThird Battle of Wezen (July 3rd - 4th).\nOn July 3rd, 2184, an Automaton attack from &lt;a href=\"Varylia%205\"&gt;Varylia 5&lt;/a&gt; reached the planet, at the same time as &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; in same sector was also struck by invasion fleet. The latter received a greater amount of troops due to its importance in Major Order, leaving Wezen to a grim fate. \nFourth Battle of Wezen July 4th - 6th).\nAfter the Automaton attack, a liberation campaign began on Wezen. However, with a more pressing defense campaign on &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X-45&lt;/a&gt; and a campaign to cut off the attack on &lt;a href=\"Meissa\"&gt;Meissa&lt;/a&gt; not many forces have been dedicated here. By July 5th, Wezen was nearly in full Automaton command. A small force of ~300 lone Helldivers is holding on by a thread to prevent the encirclement of the S.E.A.F forces in the Ymir sector, which includes over half of all Helldiver squadrons currently. Wezen fell on July 6th. 16,000 Helldivers are left surrounded in the remaining systems of the Ymir sector, desperately holding the line to protect the &lt;a href=\"X-45\"&gt;X system&lt;/a&gt;. \nOperation Liberty Crush &amp; Operation Vengeful Cleansing (August 2nd - August 4th).\nAfter the fall of Wezen, it would be under Automaton Occupation for the remainder of July, as the Helldivers would divert towards other objectives. However, Wezen wasn't lost yet as, soon after their victory at X-45, the Helldivers would manage to secure a defensive line of planets that split the bot front in half, with Wezen being within the encircled domain. As such, Super Earth High Command issued an order for the immediate recapture of the encircled planets, with Wezen as one of its key targets.\nThe battles were fierce, but despite the immense sacrifice, the Helldivers were too late in liberating Wezen, making Operation Liberty Crush a close failure, yet not completely in vain, as Wezen would still be liberated on the early hours of August 4th, during Operation Vengeful Cleansing. Furthermore the successful defence of &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;, both the &lt;a href=\"Ymir%20Sector\"&gt;Ymir&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Andromeda%20Sector\"&gt;Andromeda&lt;/a&gt; Sectors are once again securely in Super Earths hands. Whilst the Automaton's may have won the battle, strategy of dividing the bot forces is now a firm reality, with only &lt;a href=\"Troost\"&gt;Troost&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Vandalon%20IV\"&gt;Vandalon IV&lt;/a&gt; still in automaton clutches in the &lt;a href=\"Trigon%20Sector\"&gt;Trigon Sector&lt;/a&gt;, the Super Earth Armed Forces are well on their way to winning the war."}
