{"id": "4124", "revid": "31024592", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=4124", "title": "Wiki Rules", "text": "= General Rules =\nWe are aware that there are two Helldivers wikis, one on Wiki.gg and the original one here. We function as separate platforms but we are still on equal terms, this means you are not to go out of your way to be rude to their editors or steal their work.\n1. Keep it civil.\nDo not make personal attacks on other people. If you need to criticize another user\u2019s argument, do so without attacking them as a person. Do not use bigoted language, including slurs which degrade another person or group of people based on gender, race, sexual orientation, nationality, religion, etc.\n2. Plagiarism is not allowed.\nWhen adding to an article, be sure to write it in your own words unless it's taken from an official source such as in-game or from the developers. Copy/Pasting someone else's work is incredibly distasteful and isn't allowed. This, including the gathering of images, please credit the original source no matter where you got it from. \n3. Do not harass other users.\nIf somebody asks you to stop posting certain content on their wall/talk, respect their wishes. It is their profile after all.\n4. Follow community guidelines for formatting.\nWhen a community has established formatting, it\u2019s important to adhere to that, especially when spoiler content is involved.\n=Secondary Rules =\nThe Secondary Rules are still rules none the less, this means these rules are there to keep this wiki functional\n5. Do not engage in self-promotion.\nThe wiki is a collaborative community resource for the topic at hand. It is NOT a free place to advertise your related website, YouTube channel, blog, social media account, etc. Have a question about whether your link would be welcome? Ask an !\n6. Be a productive member of the wiki.\nContribute to the wiki in line with the established processes and conventions. Need help? Ask an ! Disrupting the wiki with \u201cedit warring\u201d over differing opinions of a topic with another user or group of users is not productive.\n7. Keep things as factual and official as you can.\nPersonal, fan-created lore is typically not allowed on official pages. If it cannot be proven and/or hasn't been stated by the development studio, then it shouldn't be on the pages. Exceptions can be made if the fan-created lore/information is written well enough and doesn't pose conflicting issues with other bits of lore or articles. If new information about a subject arises via official sources, the fan-made information will be removed and replaced with the proper text.\n__NOEDITSECTION__"}
