{"id": "6058", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6058", "title": "Zefia", "text": "Zefia is one of the six planets that reside in the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nTopography.\nSimilar to &lt;a href=\"Shallus\"&gt;Shallus&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tibit\"&gt;Tibit&lt;/a&gt;\nHistory.\nSecond Galactic War.\nOperation Bulwark of Democracy.\nZefia was, for most of the Second Galactic War, a peaceful planet colony that Super Earth had settled at some point after the &lt;a href=\"First%20Galactic%20War\"&gt;First Galactic War&lt;/a&gt;, serving mostly as a xenobiology outpost where scientists could research on all forms of alien fauna and flora. However, the Automatons, envious of Super Earth's progress and prosperity, would force Zefia into the conflict.\nOn September 19th, the Automatons would violently occupy the nearby planet of Clasa. However, thanks to the Helldivers' righteous interference, they would be unable to make much moves onto any of the planets connected. As such, Zefia stood on guard as it monitored the developing Automaton force on Clasa while discretely evacuating its research materials.\nFor almost a whole month, the colonists at Zefia watched Clasa closely, anticipating an attack. On October 9th, 2184, their expectations became true, as the Automatons launched an attack onto Zefia. However, in their delay, they had allowed the Helldivers to mobilize towards Zefia en masse. Zefia was successfully defended by the end of the day and allowed the Helldivers to return to other planets without much incident.\nInterim (Oct. 22nd - Oct. 23rd).\nEver since, Zefia has remained free. However, the Automatons, as baked into their programming, could not bear to see free and prosperous planets. As such, they would launch an attack onto Zefia on October 22nd, pretty much hours after their special strike force, the Jet Brigade, had been decisively defeated at &lt;a href=\"Marfark\"&gt;Marfark&lt;/a&gt;. This attack would be very well timed with an attack at &lt;a href=\"Gatria\"&gt;Gatria&lt;/a&gt; from the .\nGiven the lack of a major order, the higher priority of other operations and the remoteness of Zefia, the Automatons would encounter no resistance and would capture Zefia the next day."}
{"id": "5887", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=5887", "title": "Zegema Paradise", "text": ""}
{"id": "6059", "revid": "34624864", "url": "https://helldivers.fandom.com/wiki?curid=6059", "title": "Zosma", "text": "Zosma is one of the five planets that reside within the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt;.\nHistory.\nOperation Iron Rain.\nZosma was a peaceful and sparsely populated colony located on the galactic fringe. Mainly an afterthought in the Federation of Super Earth, its extremely cold temperatures and grey, barren ground and skies painted the world in a dark shadow in the outskirts of its galaxy. It and the rest of the &lt;a href=\"Gellert%20Sector\"&gt;Gellert Sector&lt;/a&gt; would see relatively no action or violence for the 100 years following the first galactic war.\nHowever, Super Earth's enemies would not bear to see peace and prosperity in the sector. Late in October 2184, the Gellert Sector would make an unprecedented call for help from Liberty's elite force, the Helldivers. The few colonists settled in the sector watched in horror as the &lt;a href=\"Automatons\"&gt;Automatons&lt;/a&gt;, who had just recently taken control of bordering &lt;a href=\"Zefia\"&gt;Zefia&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Yed%20Prior\"&gt;Yed Prior&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Tanis%20Sector\"&gt;Tanis Sector&lt;/a&gt;, would mount an offensive into the Gellert Sector, taking control of both &lt;a href=\"Blistica\"&gt;Blistica&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Mintoria\"&gt;Mintoria&lt;/a&gt;. The Automatons would then attempt to take &lt;a href=\"Zzaniah%20Prime\"&gt;Zzaniah Prime&lt;/a&gt;- Zosma's neighbor- but would be easily repelled by the Helldivers in an impressive display of cooperation. \nHowever, the peace of Zosma's neighbor would not last, as the Automatons would launch a combined 16 Battalions from Blistica and Mintoria towards Zzaniah Prime in late November, a much stronger invasion fleet than their first attempt. This time, the robots would be successful, as the Helldivers were concerned with a then-Major Order sending the Corps towards the Terminid front. This, coupled with Zzaniah's location on the galactic fringe, as well as a large assault on &lt;a href=\"Fenrir%20III\"&gt;Fenrir III&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"Terminids\"&gt;Terminids&lt;/a&gt;, meant that very few Helldivers would heed Zzaniah's call for aid. As such, the planet was captured on November 27, 2184. Zosma was now under severe threat, as its only connection to the rest of the galaxy was through its sandy neighbor that was now overtaken by the iron grip of the Automatons. Zosma's colonists were now hoping for the best- but preparing for the worst."}
